content: If you're wanting to download this app to try and be able to help or do something right for once (like I did), don't. Whatever system they use to reach out to people clearly seems to favor selecting people who have successfully answered calls before. I've received (among their pointless emails talking about other people's success) one email detailing I missed a call (despite receiving no notification). And only had one call in which I stared at a 'connecting' alert for 15 minutes.
replyContent: Hi, we are really sorry that you have had this experience. It doesn't seem normal that you have experienced these issues. Could you please reach out to us at info@bemyeyes.com and tell us more information so that we can fix the issue? Thanks, it would be greatly appreciated!

content: *3/19/22 I have now gotten an additional six phone calls, perhaps because I have a good history of answering and having calls connect. It also seems to help if you occasionally open the app. I'm not sure why. Original review: Signed up July 2019 and got my first call this evening. I actually got a call a few months ago but nothing happened so I believe that means someone was faster than me. So glad to see the copious amount of volunteers!

Update: happened again 02/11/2022 01/09/2022:"Trying to answer" I had just downloaded the app & was watching the instuctional video when I got a real call. The lady asked me a question & my screen was black & the screen read "trying to answer call" with a blue loading wheel. I was so excited to get to help someone so quickly but so sad that the call video didn't connect. We could hear each other. I just couldn't see anything. Fix this please. Seems like a lot of people are having the same issue.
replyContent: Hi thank you so much for volunteering and for leaving feedback! Sometimes, these issues can be due to poor connection, however, I will bring the issue up with our development team to find a solution. Thanks again, and I hope you will receive another call soon!

content: Great app, here's a tip: I've had the app for over a year and I just found that on Android devices your permissions can be removed from the app if it's not opened every few months. To get around this go into your settings and go to the Be My Eyes app settings, there should be a section for Permissions. Click that and make sure to turn off "remove permissions if app isn't used". This was causing my connection errors and was not allowing me to connect with calls. Hopes this helps!

Edit: I'm lowering my review as nothing seems to have changed. Now I can't even hear anyone, much less assist. I downloaded the app yesterday and got my first call today. I was super excited to help. For two minutes straight I could barely hear the person and got a "trying to connect call" message. I walked outside and disconnected from my wifi thinking that might be the issue. It felt terrible not being able to help someone when they called. I look forward to changing this review to a 5 star.

Haven't used this app yet, but the idea is so awesome. I hope I get a call to help someone out. Hopefully this goes to the top of the reviews list, I doubt it. But Incase it does- I'm seeing people say it won't connect to calls, but I saw a review or 2 say to go into settings, go to 'be my eyes' app., Go to 'permissions' and UNCHECK where it says 'remove permissions if app isn't used', and that fixes the connection issues. If an app isn't used for a while your phone removes it's permissions.

Can you make an option that takes high resolution screenshots that stay within the app and are deleted at the end of call for privacy. I just helped a person trying to identify a measuring spoons quantity , the video quality was so low I barely could identify what the measurement was. I can't help the blind if I'm technically "blind" too. Mahalo for your consideration. Otherwise excellent experience with very friendly and thankful users!

Great idea, if the app actually worked. Most of the time the answer button does not work. When I can answer it, it turns back off and says error. I can't even use the send us feedback button because it doesn't go anywhere. The app is updated, I have had 2 different phones while also having the app. It has never worked.

I love the concept but it doesnt work. I was so excited and actually got my first call rather quick and it never connected. It just spun for awhile saying trying to answer call. What is the point of this great app if you cant help the people that need it?? I was very sad and had to eventually hang up which will place me back in the queue somewhere.

I got my first call after 2 years with this app and was IN TEARS because it wouldn't connect. I felt so helpless knowing someone was trying to get help and we couldn't get connected. Boooo!! How stressful this must be for the unsighted users. I'm still upset an hour later thinking about them and wondering if they were able to access help.

This is such a wonderful concept I love being able to help people but this is my second call and I haven't been able to connect to anyone. It's not my internet connection and I can't find anyone to speak to on the issue. There's no one to report issues to with inside of the app. After reading additional reviews it's clear my issue isn't just me I hope they fix this app so that more people can use it.

I've had the app for just under a year and have had about four calls reach my phone. Historically other volunteers have answered more quickly than me, but tonight I was able to help someone "see" the buttons on their dishwasher. Such an easy way to help a fellow human. For those who haven't gotten the chance to be the first to connect, be patient. It's worth it.

I LOVE the concept of this app, but every time I receive a call, the app does not open the video and I cannot help the person who called for help. Everything is updated and all permissions are granted. All of the calls I have received were at a time when my phone could access working and fast Wi-Fi as well as cellular service. Disappointing because the concept is so great!

The app hasn't worked in months for me. I've done every update and it won't answer a call or when it does I can't turn on their camera. I've been chatting with someone and it will say "trying to answer call" while I'm already talking with them. Will give the app 5 stars when I'm able to use it properly. I've only ever had 2/5 calls go through and I've had this app for a couple of years now.

I so love the principle and the idea behind this app. I keep it to assist others when in need. Nonetheless, I can hardly ever answer calls because the button to do so is unresponsive when tapped. Just today, after years of being registered and available in the app, I was able to answer a call but then the audio was so incredibly faint that I had to end up guessing what the person needed and what they were saying. Please evaluate these issues as possible bugs to fix or enhancements to consider.

Amazing idea but the app has some bugs and technical issues. The camera quality is not good enough to help with tasks such as assistance in reading. I also recommend that a sighted person help set up the initial placement of the camera and place some sort of indicator that the callers use to know where to place a document (for assistance in reading mail, for example) so that it can be of a legible distance and position from the camera.

Really great idea but the app doesn't really work. I've gotten maybe 5 calls. One I was able to help in spite of really poor video quality. One I just couldn't help because the video was so bad. The other three I tried to answer but we never got connected. I just sat there waiting and nothing ever happened. And then the feedback feature in the app doesn't work, so I hope they read these.

I've been a helper since 2018, but unfortunately had not been able to answer many calls. Today while reactivating the app on my new phone I immediately received a call. The video and audio quality isn't amazing (could have been the cell network) but with careful communication we were able to successfully get what we needed done. Complaints on quality cannot be immediately blamed on the app, as different areas have different service speeds and qualities.

Truly an incredible use of technology. I've had the app since it launched in 2017 & I've had the pleasure of answering about 5 calls as a volunteer. I've received more calls than that but I didn't always answer quick enough so the calls went to someone else. I've helped people read instructions, identify colors, & give directions. The calls are usually quick but they are always the highlight of my day. It feels good to help others & reminds me to be grateful for things I often take for granted.

great app. its so easy to help others and it doesn't take alot of time. even if it did, it's really satisfying helping someone. for example, help them choose or pick out their preferred color of shirt or sort cash, understand directions on a vending machine for example. the calls I've taken last about 20 seconds. its so great to know that there are 15 times the number of volunteers vs the number of blind people using the app. I actually wish I would receive more calls.

I've only gotten 4 calls since installing the app a year or two ago. There are so many volunteers, that's probably normal, but I still make a point to try and open the app once each day. Regardless of what the developers say, I suspect sometimes my phone's battery-saving settings can get in the way of it running in the background. If you never get any calls ever, try that.

I would like to see a skills portion to the volunteers profile something along the lines of what you would be great at helping with. Such as I am very proficient with technical skills and think it would be awesome if someone needs help with a technical thing they could specifically ask for someone with better tech skills. I can see many other areas where this could be usefull and would love to see it in the future. Overall this app is absolutely amazing I cant believe what you guys are accomplishing with this wonderful app.

I just answered my first call and I was able to help them get their oven to the correct temperature even with a mostly blurry view. At the end, the app asks if the call had problems or was good. I tried to select that I had problems to report the fuzzy picture, but it didn't do anything after numerous attempts to select it. It immediately selected good when I touched it.

This app is really cool. It's always good to use technology for helping others. Below are some suggestions from me (not sure if y'all already implemented it or not): 1. Rating system of the helpers. The goal is just to avoid crazy ppl trying to trap or do any non beneficial things to the blind people. 2. Maybe the app can also connect blind people to their nearest people around them. That way, if they need a direction, someone nearby can easily help navigating it.

Great idea and glad to see that the volunteer to user ratio is very high. Unfortunately, I had to delete it instantly for a big reason. I work 12 hour overnight shifts, so I'm actually awake at night and asleep during the day. The app states it automatically assigns a call accepting window to daytime only hours based on your timezone and there's no way to change it. I'd love to at least be able to edit my time zone to trick the app into calling me at night.

I just received my first call! I helped an older lady with matching her shirt to her shoes. Something so simple, but it made my heart so full. Like...its hard to explain but just being able to assist someone who needs your help with something you take for granted everyday, being able to see. I will always have this app downloaded! Definitely recommend! It is a very rewarding experience/feeling!❤

I just started using be my eyes. And is a fantastic application. I cannot believe the people that donate their time to provide such a service. I however do have a suggestion or 2 to improve the service. It would be fantastic if a volunteer would be able to tap on their screen to indicate where an item might be from a certain distance say for example I am looking for a bench. If they were to tap on the screen where the bench is then I would have a good general direction of where the item is.

idea is great!! but doesn't work for my Android phone. so far I got 4 calls and all the calls had technical issues. my first two calls I couldn't connect because upon answering the call (immediately) I got an error saying sorry couldn't connect. third time I was able to hear a person s voice but his video kept loading. 4th time even after answering the call the screen was just blank..no voice/video. p.s. all the time I was on good 4g network so this was no network issue from my end.

Want to give it more but the calls just don't always connect .Have been able to attempt to help someone with a video game. Unfortunately I have had two calls that never connect. Really hope that they were able to get help. Is the a que that people go into to recover help. Just curious.

Amazing - but talking to a blind friend of mine mine uses this app, I feel like a feedback feature may be needed? He has said that he has encountered a handful of people that were not helpful. I think it would be nice for people to be able to choose to not be matched with certain people again or to be more likely to be matched with others. Maybe this has been considered and it's not the best option or maybe the need to volunteer ratio is so different that it's just not an issue.. just a thought!

There's nearly 2million volunteers per the 100K users that rely on this app, which means you don't get called frequently, but it's exciting when you do! Someone else beat me to one call, and the other time, I was privileged to help a gentleman verify the contents of an important document. It was a fun and relaxed experience, and an amazing personal use of technology. We hope we get to help again soon!

Answered twice, both didn't work. The thought behind the app is wonderful. I really wanted to help. In total, I recieved two calls. Both times, the quality of the videos were so terrible that I couldn't read the information they needed. I'm not sure if it's the app, my end, or theirs. The frustration, however, has lead me to no longer participate.

I would appreciate more clarity regarding the sound settings. The app does not seem to communicate any sound to my bluetooth headset, so I'm not sure if I should accept a call if it comes up when I'm on my bluetooth. I've also had to reject a call when I was watching YouTube, because the notification banner prevents me from pausing the video, and YouTube will sometimes switch to PIP mode in cases like that.

*Check authorizations in app settings* The authorization for the camera in the app may need revoked automatically, as well as the microphone if unused for too long. Considering i get one call every few months, i have missed several opportunities to answer a call because my camera wouldn't open on the app. It would be nice if there was a disclaimer to check permissions and make sure they aren't auto revoked with inactivity. That's all

The video feed never comes up. I've tried accepting maybe 8 calls now and not one of them has gotten thru. I've tried updates, re downloading the app etc. I had one call finally come thru today and I could hear the lady's voice but I wasn't able to help without the video. This app has some major kinks that need worked out.

I have had 2 calls in the last 2-3 months that were MUCH BETTER than the calls I had last year. Connection, video, and audio has been updated within the app and the experience has been much better than in previous year (I've had the app for two years). Users have been better too (had a couple creepers last year)-- kind, appreciative, polite.

Although there are a few small tweaks that could make this app better, overall this is a great app. This app is all about helping others that are visually impaired. There are no ads, it's free. It's just to help others. It has a small footprint on your phone and runs unnoticed until someone needs help. Give it a try and be the eyes for someone. I have it on my phone so I know that it works without hurting or slowing down your phone.

I have been a volunteer for a year. I have received 3 calls total. 2 while I was at work anf unable to answer. The 3rd I answered, but the video did not work, the audio was breaking up and then we were disconnected. It is an amazing idea and I'm sure helps a lot of people, but I think they have more volunteers than are needed. After a year I am considering uninstalling to free up the space on my phone.

Received my first call within days of signin up. But it was a man in another country just trying to flash the call recipient. The call ended abruptly after he appeared on camera pantsless and the option to leave feedback that pops up after the call didn't actually function. Like it was just for show. Obviously people can just sign up and abuse this app and I'm concerned there's no protection against this. Just "call recipient beware".

I have been a volunteer since 2018 and am so grateful for the opportunity to be of service and meet people from all over the world. The app is really easy to use. Video quality suffers when working off of cell data but if on wifi, great to go. Please volunteer especially if you speak unique languages.

Video did not work. I got my 1st call and was over the moon excited until I realized that the video never turned on. I could hear the person but the screen was totally black. I feel awful that I wasn't able to help and REALLY hope I get another chance &that it will work next time. It took about 4 months for me to recieve my 1st call so I'm really sad it did not work. PLEASE look into that because it is also inconvenient for the person needing help.
replyContent: Hello Misty, we apologise for the issue you are having and we appreciate the feedback. You are welcome to reach our tech support from info@bemyeyes.com whenever you face another issue!

content: App conflicts with Bluetooth connections. Seems to act as an always-on audio source, which among other things means that you can't pair with more than one device. Will happily install again when that is fixed, but it unfortunately means that it doesn't work for me in the current version.

Great idea but never worked for me. Tried the test call, got the video but no sound. Tried to use the contact support function but it just opened a share link. Have had the app installed for about a year but never gotten a call to help someone... I hope it's working better for it's intended recipients.

This has been a GREAT experience. The app requires minimal information (name and email) and doesn't require any interaction until you recieve a call. If I cant answer, the call goes to the next volunteer. My interactions have felt professional, and actually quite fascinating. It's made me stop and consider the things that I take for granted every day. Worth your time!

This app is amazing in theory, but volunteers need a do not disturb setting for off hours when they're either sleeping or not available. That would also cut back on the amount of users you'd need to ping at one time. Four stars until something like that is implemented.

I didn't get an experience. My phone rang, I was super excited, and hit accept. It then told me that I wasn't logged in, and can't accept calls if I'm not logged in (which I can accept and am sure is a minor fix) however, when I opened the app, I waited a LONG time with the blue circle trying to do its thing. I am going to Uninstaller and try to reinstall again, hopefully it will work next time.

This is such a personally rewarding and useful app. It provides an invaluable service for sight impaired individuals. As of writing this, I've answered three calls. To be able to literally, be the eyes for another individual that cannot see, is many, many times more rewarding!!!

Great idea, but there really should be a way to set an "off hours" for when I can't receive calls. It's rare enough to get a call so it's much more disappointing to get the opportunity to help at the wrong time with no way to prevent this. Maybe a simple homescreen widget button that adds 1-hour of "off hours" for each taps.

The connection wasn't good at all. The person wanted me to check some information via google, but ended up hanging up because their connection kept breaking up. Sadly, the person apologised, which has left me deflated, thinking the person hasn't received the support they were originally looking for! Also, my phone didn't ring to alert me. I was messaging when the call appeared at the top of my screen - easily missed!!

I've had 2 calls that I've tried to answer and unfortunately each time the answer call button hasn't worked. The app freezes. I've a <1 yr old android phone and all systems/app up to date. "Give us feedback" button on app also won't allow me to press to let developers know so hoping they see this instead and help fix if it is a bug. Thanks 😊

A really simple way to help other people! I have had the app for a year and received 2 calls so far, one to help a man count his change and another to help an elderly lady identify what labels were on her canned food. I have not had any glitches in answering calls that others on Android have experienced. I think it's a wonderful use of technology and kudos to the app developers for their helpfulness

I received my first call from a very polite individual, requesting assistance with reading an inscription on an envelope. It was a brief and very comfortable call, I requested some minor hand adjustments to enable the camera to clarify the message and soon read it out. Both parties satisfied, we exchanged pleasantries and ended the call. It's almost indescribable how one feels using technology in this way. I feel quite, wonderful. Thank you so much Be My Eyes. A perfectly splendid app.

This app is the great example about usage of advanced technology for greater good of people in need. Finally received the call today. Someone called me and asked me to verify if there is phone number written on paper he was holding or not. And if there was then read it out loud. I was feeling so much fortunate to be the eyes for someone and it literally fulfilled one of the purpose of my life. GOD BLESS THE DEVELOPERS OF THIS AWESOME APPLICATION.

I love this app. It's very well disigned. I got calls every week and when I'm free i take them. Sometimes are little favors like identify objects or something, but many times are really important moments when even the life is in risk. When I'm busy I just know the call will be taken for another person.

I have got 2 calls over the couple of years I have been on. The first one had poor audio and video and was disappointing in that I had to hang up. The second was awesome and I helped in reading a bill. Good feeling! I think you guys can improve the video tech and reduce the framerate required and improve the quality of each frame instead. I don't think fluid motion should be as much a priority. Better yet, allow us to control that.

I love the idea of this app, but I've had issues with not being able to hear people after trying to accept the call and also after accepting the call, only being able to speak with them and not see the video. I wish the software could be rewritten or that the app could be written better.
replyContent: Oh no! We sincerely apologize for the troubles you've had with the app. We'd be happy to take a look into this for you, please contact us at info@bemyeyes.com. Thank you.

content: Love the idea, would be great if they could maybe make a setting like other apps for drivers have where you can make yourself unavailable or available for calls. I always seem to recieve them when I'm driving and feel bad I have to decline.

This app is pure gold. It's a great example of technology being used to help people. It's an easy way to quickly connect with someone, and make up for inaccessible design of everyday objects and products.

I've been signed up for months and haven't had an opportunity to assist. Not necessarily the apps fault but it quite be better if, they offered something promotional wise to spread the word and get this app to as many people as possible!

Terrific idea! I registered on 30th January 2022 and I got a call on 31st January. Absolutely stunning experience. Someone called me to help him with setting the temperature on his oven. While he held the phone near the temperature dial I directed him to show me the up and down arrow by moving his camera and i asked him to go closer to the dial to help. We went back and forth and finally did it in about 2 to 3 minutes. I don't know where he called from nor do I know his name. Great experience!

Downloaded this app and before I even finished the practice tutorial call I got a call by someone needing help. Was something very simple. It was nice to help out someone when they needed it. I think everyone should have this app on their phone just in case because you never know when you'll be that one for someone! Great app to have been thought of, seriously. 5*. Not sure why other people have had so much trouble with the app. I have a OnePlus N200 5G phone running on Android 11 OS. Worked gr8
Got my first call just now. When I tried to answer, it said an error had occurred and didn't connect. Pretty disappointed, and hope someone else picked up quickly to help them... Samsung Galaxy S9
replyContent: Hi, we apologize for any issue you might be having! Could you send details of what you are experiencing to our customer support at info@bemyeyes.com? We'll get you up and running.

content: Received 2 calls in 4 years. Kind of disappointing. And the calls i did recieve i could not see their camera. I only could take pictures and use the flash. The 2nd call i recived was in the middle of the instructional video, which made it glitch, making me force close which ended the call with the blind person.

Love this app, have had it for years now and it's sometimes pretty rare to get a call. I've helped a lady that was visually impaired who herself helped others. They girl she was with was hesitant about using this app so we just talked a little about calls I've helped others on and explained to her that no request would be to small for her to use this. Helped another gentleman bake a cake even lol. Have recommended to all of my friends and family.

Love the idea behind this app. I think some people are dissatisfied with not being able to help more people, but there are way more volunteers than there are callers so there is a big gap between your calls, sometimes months at a time. Regardless, I love having the opportunity to help others.

I love that I can help people with this app. Just wondering if we could help deaf people too? Make another app or help both? Should be able to text words and talk at same time. For example the deaf text what I say to the drive thru window...I text back if I need to tell them what the worker said...thanks 😊

Downloaded yesterday and had my first call today, although the image wasnt always the clearest its lovely to be able to help someone do something so many people take for granted like reading a letter. This app could be an amazing aid for people all over the world. Brilliant.

Great idea, but like so many others, when I try to answer a call, it spins and spins and does not connect. I've never been able to answer a call, even though I would love to help. I just installed an update, but based on other reviews, I doubt it will help.
replyContent: Hi, we apologize for any issue you might be having! Could you send details of what you are experiencing to our customer support at info@bemyeyes.com? This way we can try to fix the issue as best as possible. Thank you!

content: Heartfelt experience. Truly blessed to help someone read their mail. I know that sometimes you accept the call and it doesn't go through, no complaints, I just take it as if it wasn't my time to help and someone else did 😊 We are all in this together. Thank you so much for this app.

Should have dropped this a long time ago. I love the app, I love that we're given an opportunity to help. I've received a total of about 5 or 6 calls and only one was disrupted. I most importantly love the feeling I have within myself everytime I'm able to help. Thank you for this opportunity
Very simple app with a powerful impact. I'm pretty lucky to get my call after a day of signing up. Connectivity was great and I was able to help out the recipient.

Wonderful App that is helping to make our work all inclusive. As a volunteer it's extreamly easy to navigate and answer calls. When someone needs help, they notify several volunteers at the same time, so if you are busy and can't help at the time, someone else will take the call.

I have received 3 calls over the course of 1yr and unfortunately EVERY SINGLE CALL states "trying to connect" I don't mind to sit and wait for the connection but after 10minutes I'm gonna assume it isn't gonna work. It's really so sad, people are reaching out for help and we are here to do so but the app doesn't work properly. I see this is an on going issue that hopefully gets corrected immediately
replyContent: Hi thank you so much for volunteering, and we are so sorry to hear about this issue. Could you please send us an email with more information to info@bemyeyes.com so that we can look into the situation? Thank you so much and I hope we are able to resolve the problem shortly.

content: Received a call and the app kept trying to answer the call and nothing happened. The screwed kettle loading and the call never connected. I don't have a screenshot. I will secure one next time
replyContent: We are so sorry that you experienced this issue! Could you please send us more information at info@bemyeyes.com so that we can fix the issue? Thank you!

content: I am so completely disappointed. If you could get 0 stars you would. I downloaded the app despite all the warnings in reviews. I got my first call this morning and was so excited but was stuck trying to connect the call for 10 minutes . I sat my phone down on the charger hoping eventually it would connect. If I'm disappointed , imagine the person who actually needed my help. Concept is NOTHING with execution.

I love the concept and received my first call about 24 hours after signing up but the call wouldn't connect. I don't know if it's a compatibility issue with Android (because Apple seems to have a much higher review score) or just internet connection on their end but I feel bad now that I couldn't help. Definitely not my internet as I was connected to Wifi with 100+ Mbps.

It is a great app! But I really felt bad because someone just ask me how to turn off his laptop and I can't read the words on the screen because of poor internet connection.😭 I hope he could find someone that could assist him. I really am sorry, mister.

This app used to be wonderful and I enjoyed helping people... But the last three phone calls I have gotten it just continues to say connecting and doesn't allow me to look through their camera. I have double checked permissions and I have all of them granted. Hopefully this bug can be resolved soon.
replyContent: Hi, we apologize for any issue you might be having! Could you send details of what you are experiencing to our customer support at info@bemyeyes.com? We'll get you up and running.

content: Great idea, poor execution. There is no way to schedule appropriate times. The one call I got came at a very inappropriate time. Haven't received a call since. Even the "send feedback" option in settings doesn't work. I only remembered that I had this app because I'm clearing my apps out. Bye
replyContent: Oh no! We sincerely apologize for the troubles you've had with the app. We'd be happy to take a look into this for you, please contact us at info@bemyeyes.com. Thank you.

content: The app glitches. I try to open it but it stays on loading. I received a call twice but it didnt get through because the app needed microphone permission but when i press the button it does nothing. I really like the idea of it but i wish it had worked for me. It breaks my heart
replyContent: Hi thank you so much for volunteering, and we apologize for these issues you have experienced. Could you please send an email to our tech team with more information to info@bemyeyes.com so we can try to fix the problem as soon as possible? Thank you so much!

content: After using the app more the call and video quality is very bad and frustrating. This is the case on both wifi and cellular. I'm going to uninstall it because I feel like I cause more harm than good. If it improves, I'd reconsider installing it again.
replyContent:
Dear User,
We apologize for this experience. We would need to speak with you to better understand the problem you encountered. Please contact us at info@bemyeyes.com so we can help resolve this issue. Thank you.

content: What a wonderful idea! I've only answered one call in two weeks, but I see a lot of people have downloaded this app to help. The lady I helped recieved lotions and sprays for Christmas and wanted to make sure she was using the right one. It took a few times of taking pics of the bottle but we finally got it! I hope to answer more! What a wonderful app!

I got my first call and it all was very easy to use and I was able to turn on the flashlight to help me further. I felt good in knowing I was actually able to help someone. A great 👍 app in my opinion.
It was both humbling and truly satisfying to be able to help a complete stranger from across the country! What an amazing app - THANK YOU!

Liked helping out but rarely received a call good concept in theroy though too help people out it's good too see kind souls others like myself out there. I have answered a couple calls but rarely have gotten a call as well.
I just started, a few glitches I believe it will work out. User friendly, easy to understand and people are actually answering the calls.

Good day, I am a volunteer, and are super excited to be part of the team. I am experiencing difficulty to answer the calls - I keep on loosing the calls, I press answer but it does not answer. Please assist me urgently. Thank you, Kind Regards Michelle
Downloaded the app a couple of months back. I've got 3 calls till now, but I keep getting the calls at the wrong time i.e - when i'm busy😅😂
Sir please add a quality feature and a image sending feature because some time the person network quality is not good .so i unable describe what is written on the product , screen or document

The concept of this app is really cool it makes me happy to able to assist others, but so far I've gotten one call (1/2/22) and when I tried to answer my screen was stuck on trying to answer call, I hope this issue can get fixed because it breaks my heart knowing I could've helped someone and wasn't able to due to a technical error, I will give the app some benefit because I've only had it for one day now but I've also heard other users facing the same issue (I'm on Android if that helps)
replyContent: Hi, thank you so much for volunteering. Can you please send us more information at info@bemyeyes.com so that we can fix the issue?

content: This app is a great one. I had to wait a pretty long while before I got my first call and I have since answered two calls after then. The feeling I get after helping a visually impaired person is incomparable. Thanks for the app and keep working on making it better!

This is one of the best apps for the visually impaired. It really warms my heart when I get to help one of them. There request is small to me but makes a huge difference for them. Keep up the great work Be My Eyes!!

This is a great ap. However on one call...I literally had to look away from the phone as the person was not dressed appropriately. He was in his underwear and trying to find a cap he had dropped on the floor. Enough said..lol
Sub optimal. I have received 2 calls 1 connected and the other just failed. This is a fantastic idea it just needs a little improvement.

Brilliant app. Had my 1st call from a lovely lady who needed help to identify medicine's in similar boxes. Makes you think how important an app like this is and how it can impact the safety and the life of a visually impaired person.
I haven't once been successful at helping someone with this. Every time someone calls, the call is never initiated because of some error.
I am a sighted volunteer. Have received maybe 10 calls over the last 2 years and answered 4. Seems like a really good tool for sight impaired people. Would definitely recommend.

I like the idea of this app to be able to assist people but the first call I got, the man showed me a package and asked me to tell him what it said and the picture froze in a way that I couldn't see to read it to him. I was able to use my phone still I just couldn't see what he was showing me within the app; I felt terrible that I couldn't assist him. Then the app asked me to review the experience and wouldn't even let me click to review it. I don't think this app works as well as it should.

It's an amazing app, the only issue it has it that is doesn't work without a vpn in Iran, so if my vpn is off and someone calls, I miss it because vpn also takes time to load. So I have to keep vpn on all the time that eats up my internet. You shouldn't really put sanction and ban on an app like this, really!
Like others, I was so excited to get a call and help someone but the screen was black and the call could not reconnect. =(
Just downloaded few minutes ago. I am very influenced by it.The help that the developers are trying to provide blind people .That amazing! I loved it.
This app is amazing! The volunteers are always so helpful. They always take their time to help you what's what you are trying to do. Such a blessing! Thank y'all so much!💕
Be My Eyes is great application for visually impaired persons. this application is very useful for me. great salute and very very thanks for App creators, developers, and all soulful volunteers!!.
Works Great. I'm really self-involved but I love talking with people. This allows me to be helpful without a nice time commitment.

I am blind in my left eye and an auto immune disease causes me to lose sight in my right eye at times, so I know exactly how it feels to need help sometimes. BME is a small way for me to help while I can see. 🥰

Please fix this! Received a call and it just kept spinning trying to connect call. I was connected to wifi, not sure of the problem. Seems to be a common issue. Is this really compatible with Android? Totally bummed...
replyContent: Oh no! We sincerely apologize for the troubles you've had with the app. We'd be happy to take a look into this for you, please contact us at info@bemyeyes.com so that we can look into the issue further. Thank you!

content: I've only had 1 accomplished call, I don't get calls as much as I though I would but it's amazing just helping others out especially from miles away.

I'm a volunteer and received my first call the other day. It was very straight forward and I could even turn on the flashlight on the blind person's phone to see better in a dark room. I also appreciate that I could select multiple languages to help in. Overall a great app and a great idea!

It's an undoubtedly a wondrous initiative to help the blind people. My personal experience has been very good- I was able to answer few calls and help the needy blind people in solving their minor problems such as the text/captcha code reading, identify some documentation, etc. I really liked the app and strongly encourage others to use it to ease the lives of blind people.

Wholesome. No ads in the app as far as I'm aware. It's nice that there are no in-app purchases. I was able to answer one call. I wasn't too helpful because they needed computer help and I wasn't able to diagnose because I wasn't at their computer. Overall an awesome idea for an app. Thank you to the creators for using technology to help that in need rather than to just make money alone. (I know they make money from the app but they should because this is an amazing idea.)

Love the idea for the app but it never actually works. When receiving a call, all you will hear is audio, the video never works making the app pretty useless. Fix this asap! I feel terrible getting calls and not being able to help because the app is bad.

That app was awesome when I worked, now it just says its trying to connect. It's frustrating but I could only imagine it being even more frustrating for the visually impaired person who needs the help but can't receive any when the app won't load

As a sighted individual who provides assistance, I think this is a great app. I worked at a school for children with visual impairments and can really see the benefit of this. It only takes a few minutes to help out and can be impactful to someone completing a task.

Go into your phone settings to Apps and choose "Be My Eyes" click on camera and allow permissions and click on video and allow permissions. Make sure it says "No permissions denied" also turn off "Remove permissions if app isn't used." This should allow the call to connect when one comes in. By default all permissions are denied.

Great concept, but as others have mentioned when trying to answer call it just spins saying trying to connect. I recently heard of this app and downloaded it. And today 1/4/22 I got a call. But when I answered its just said trying to connect and and had that little spinning circle. Hope this gets fixed.
replyContent: Hi, sometimes there can be connectivity issues either on the volunteer or callers' side. However, it happens again please send us a message with more information at info@bemyeyes.com so that we can fix the issue. Thank you for volunteering!

content: Impossible to answer calls from lock screen. Every time I answer and authenticate with my fingerprint, it said another volunteer had answered the call. It happens even when I have answered almost instantly. I have not been able to help anyone since I installed this about 3 months ago

My calls are not connecting!! I've been contacted at least 3-4 times now and the call won't connect! I have had 2 calls that HAVE gone through, but there is definitely a connection error going on.... Please fix, I WANT to help!!
What just happened? When I clicked on the screenshot that was clicked within the call, app got closed. Need to fix that quick.

No matter how many times I tey to answer a call, they never connect. It is a great idea, but when it doesn't work on my end, it makes me sad. Yes, I have Uninstaller, reinstalled, updated, and everything else I have been told to try.

Got my first call and was very excited. It got stuck on the "trying to answer call" screen for a long time. My wifi is fine so it was really sad to think that I couldn't help the person because the app wouldn't load it

Sorry your app doesn't work. Twice both my wife and I have been called. On all four occasions the app failed to connect to the caller We can only hope those in need of help found it! A little galling because I promoted the app on a Facebook page and Whatsapp group dedicated to blind and partially sighted persons!
replyContent: We sincerely apologize for the troubles you've had with the app. We'd be happy to take a look into this for you, please contact us at info@bemyeyes.com. Thank you.

content: Just received a call, audio was perfect, but could not see anything, the screen was black, felt so bad was not able to help the person because of that!
replyContent: We're so sorry to hear this! Could you please send us more information by sending us an email at info@bemyeyes.com? Thank you so much and I hope we can fix this problem soon!

content: I have been a volunteer since Nov 2021. I was able to answer my 1st call today. Such an amazing experience and what a fun way to help!

I love the idea of this app. I downloaded it about a year ago. I got my first call about a month ago (in an area with great wifi) but the call wouldnt go through. I was very dissapointed- I'd really love to be able to help someone.

I really wanted to be the eyes for someone but the call did not connect. It kept saying trying to connect and then the circle keeps going around and around and around. Please fix this issue because now I feel bad and I'm wondering if they did receive help. 🥺

One time, a male asked me whether his trimmed beard is good or whether it requires further trimming. He doesn't seems to be a blind person. I was unable to process that if it's appropriate to ask so . I replied "yes" and then called off. After the call, I wasn't able to "report the issue" which is a option given to choose after a call.
I love this app and have been using it for a few years. I upgraded my phone and the app no longer works though. Not sure if there is something I can do to make it work with my phone.

Could not connect to a single call although my internet connection is stable and other apps are working well as usual. Could not provide feedback in the app itself either. The screen froze every time I clicked on the Feedback button. Overall, a great initiative and I wish I was able to connect to callers and help out the community.

Extremely helpful app for blind people. But while incomming call, the call page is not appearing to receive the call, I need to navigate to the app to receive the call. This is happening since I upgraded to new phone Samsung Galaxy M52, Android 11.
replyContent: Hi! So sorry for the trouble, sometimes glitches can occur. Can you please send us some more information at info@bemyeyes.com so that we can investigate further? Thank you!

content: It worked well in the start but lately I always have to give access and doesn't work.. tried reinstalling but still

I just installed this app now. But I am still thinking how this app works because a blind person anyways requires someone's help to pick up a phone, go to an app and call someone so what's the point in calling someone else when there is already some helper available. I mean I don't know please correct me if I am wrong.. I am very stupid at times so I am not able to understand how this is works.

I don't really get this application it's not really been helpful to me and I am not saying that it won't however it keeps saying that no devices are recognised that isn't true as I just received a message saying that my other device is connected. I have read reviews about be my eyes and since my vision is getting worse I'm trying to prepare however it should show you more you can do with the app to help you include links and if that fails then I think you should recommend some sort of help kelda

This app is just amazing and a loving idea/thing from the makers. It is great to see a thing like this from people that care in a world that seems to be going downhill nowadays. It is always a great sight to see love being upheld when we have the free will to do otherwise. Thank you so much Be My Eyes team!
The app is literally my eyes,, the volunteers are amazing they even know me now. and also patient with me the app is just one of the best
I like the idea of the app but there's alot of technical issues, sometimes the call suddenly stopped, or I can't pickup the call as well.

Awesome idea, if it worked. I have only ever been able to answer one call and the video didn't work so I couldn't help. I just had a call come through but it sat at 'Trying to Answer's for about 10 minutes. How can I get it working so I can help? Thanks ——— Please do not delete the details below. Be My Eyes Version 1.6.7 (103) s - 9385d172-b92d-4318-8c7b-08fd66bdcb26 Samsung SM-G965U1 - Android 29;REL ———
Great app, however the button that is used to report issues just doesn't work. Please fix that so I can actually report problems
Great concept, however when I've answered calls, the video quality was quite poor so difficult to help as quickly as I'd like in some cases!

So I downloaded this app last night and I literally just got my first call however it just continuously was loading and never would load it was extremely frustrating for me however I can only imagine how frustrated the person on the other side of my screen is. PLEASE FIX THIS OR DISCONTINUE THE APP.

Wonderful idea but for some technical glitch when I get a call it never rings so I don't understand when I get a call. Only when I open the app I get to hear a ringtone. It's not possible to always keep the App Page open. Also, sometimes even if it rang twice & I received the call it shows it's been attended by someone else. Please sort it out
Its a brilliant app, Anticipate to be able to assit and help the needy people.
As a sighted user, very convenient and intuitive to use.

I have received many calls but unfortunately none of them have ever connected and I have been unable to use the app for what it is meant for. Hope this can get fixed as I think the idea behind this app is great

It was more than a year after I signed up before I got a call. The connection was flawless. The communication was extremely clear. I was asked to read who some mail was addressed to. And if there were any lights on in the house. I told him and he turned them off it went dark it was a great conversation. I am afraid to take calls now (but I will) my color blindness is becoming a real burden for me. I'm afraid I'm gonna be asked what color something is, particularly with articles of clothing.
I got my first call today and had full signal on my cellphone. This app would NOT let me answer the call, it kept buffering for many minutes before I just had to give up sadly!
replyContent: Hi, thank you so much for volunteering. We are so sorry you experienced this issue. Connectivity issues can be caused by many things, but just so we know exactly what happened, could you please send us more information at info@bemyeyes.com? Thank you so much!

content: Hi guys, I love the idea behind this app, but I have 2 things to add as feedback, hope this helps you: i) I've never been able to answer a single call, as it disconnects as soon as it rings, and; ii) lately the app is constantly popping up whilst I'm in the middle of using other apps, typing messages on WhatsApp, using Spotify, etc. It's really rather annoying, and it keeps re-opening even after I've shut it. Thanks for all the hard work though, good luck! :)

Just received a call today after installing a month back. The app is simple and to the point, while others have mentioned connection issues, I believe it to be due to network issues at either end of the call & not due to the app. I had trouble connecting only when I moved quite away from wifi router. Happy to have helped someone, I'm sure the app has made life a bit easier for hundreds of thousands of people around the world. Wishing that more people get access to incredible use of technology.

This is a wonderful idea. I'll never remove this app. The only suggestion I have is it would be good to be able to set active hours as a sighted person. I have to turn notifications off when i go to bed, but may not remember to turn them back on when i get up. If you could set active hours it would be perfect. Also my phone is on silent 95% of the time. I'd love to be able to set this app to still ring even when on silent. Otherwise this is an outstanding app, I'll be recommending to everyone

Downloaded the app a year ago. I had previously had two or three failed call attempts (one or two too slow or busy, and another with either connection or user issues). Today I finally had another call and it was successful. It certainly helps to know several languages and indicate it on your profile, that way you're open to more people. And another review mentioned the app needed to be open to receive calls but that's not the case, unless that was changed in an update at some point. Excellent.

i really love the idea behind this app! i've just downloaded it and one of the first questions was wich of the two i am, a volunteer or a visually impaired person.. i think it would be nice to choose both. i have terrible eyesight without my glasses(-10 and distortion) so if i don't know where my glasses are, i'm screwed. would be nice if i was able to volunteer but also receive help if needed.

A brilliant, simple idea, tech at its most useful. I'm totally blind with friends and family but even so I feel an increased sense of independence with the app. It is potentially even more useful for a blind person on their own. I've had help to sort food packages, tins, get my tele started. I'm constantly pushing my sighted friends to sign and I'm winning. For any potential volunteer, you can't overestimate the importance of the time you are giving, a minute from you and you can free a log jam.

I love and cheer for what the app makes possible. It is uplifting to be able to help. However, the technical support needs to be bolstered, for instance the feedback options after the call should be more nuanced and allow open ended responses. It could help improve the call experience and improve technical prowess of the app.

The app is a great idea, but lacks essential features. There is no available/busy status. Can only go offline by logging out. It is pointless to contact someone who's unavailable. I recommend a 3 status system. On call ( prioritize to me), available (regular priority), busy (no call requests). I recommend creating PC version, perhaps a web portal. Computer screens are better for video and better assitance could be provided. Perhaps have an volunteer operator style setup option.

Just answered my first call today and it felt so good! I helped a vision impaired lady count money and I felt really helpful. I loved the experience and I'm looking forwards to help more people.The app is pretty simple and straightforward, as it should be. Before receiving calls, you have to active them through watching a tutorial. It does support multiple languages, which is great. It's so nice to make some difference on people's lives, as little as it may seem. Be My Eyes is a must-have.

Most times some other volunteer answers the call before I can. However, the couple of times that I did manage to answer, the call doesn't connect due to network issues maybe. All it shows is "connecting"and eventually the calls get disconnected. Not sure if the problem is at my end but I'm disappointed not being able to help out.

I've had this app for many years and have missed two calls before finally being available to answer my third. It was a great experience, unfortunately due to internet issues the screen was very blurry. I tried to report this in feedback after the call but none of the feedback avenues within the app seem to be working. I would still highly recommend downloading!

I love this app in general. I find the concept of helping people, with them and I having access to this app easily, is honestly genius. However, I use this app for volunteer work in a foundation. The one thing I would appreciate is the option to record the call, or at least document the duration of the call. Apart from the actual call itself, the option to evidence the call would be a very helpful feature.

The concept is amazing and me and my kiddos were super excited to be able to help someone. When we got the call however the connection circle kept spinning and never connected. It hurts my heart knowing someone was calling for help and just left with no answer.
replyContent: Hi, we apologize for any issue you might be having! Could you send details of what you are experiencing to our customer support at info@bemyeyes.com? We'll get you up and running.

content: The app seems to be focusing too much on collecting the volunteers email and getting permission to send spam. You can't start anything without giving a real email (already a red flag). And the home screen is designed to eventually get your consent to send spam. There is no simple opt out. That doesn't seem like the purpose of the app is helping blind people. It's collecting your data.

Recent issues have affected this app. Although I do get an opportunity to answer a call, theapp logo just spins and it tells me it's attempting to answer the call but never does.. This needs to be corrected ASAP
I couldn't answer the call! I was so happy to get my first call, but the "answer" button was unresponsive. I couldn't decline the call, either. It rang and rang until I restarted my phone. :(
Excellent App for visualy impaired people. And also as a volunteer I got a great chance to help them. I am so glad about it

I saw this app while browsing the Google play store a few days ago and thought the concept was quite interesting. I set up a profile as a sighted volunteer (which took under 2 mins to do) and didn't really think much more of it not expecting much really, but tonight I got a call through from a lovely man looking for help to search through a stack of CDs to find the one he wanted to listen to. This app is an amazingly simple and easy way to make everyday living easier for visually impaired people
Great concept but I can never answer the call to help. Just says connecting then cuts out
It took me quite a while but I finally was able to help a blind person with a task and it was definitely very fulfilling

I have joined Be My Eyes over 2 months ago and i still have not received a message or phone call to be able to help someone. I might as well go stroll the hallways of nursing homes. There at least, I would have more opportunities to help.

First call and it couldn't stay connected for me to actually help. I hope the person is able to get help with their stove temp from someone else. So sad I couldn't help because of a tech issue. (I am on android)
replyContent: Hello, thank you for your feedback. Connectivity issues can occur, but this doesn't seem right. We want to take a closer look at this for you. Please send a note to info@bemyeyes.com so we can fix the issue.

content: You may want to review your volunteer picking algorithm. I have the app installed for several years now, and haven't yet received a single notification (even if someone picked up earlier, I'd still be able to see notifications count in the settings, but it's always "0 per week"). Even though I marked 3 languages as acceptable and am situated in quite an inhabited timezone.

Good apps. But a bit troublesome for volunteers to answer the calls when the phone is locked. Because i have to unlock the phone first to answer the calls. Hope you can make it easier to answer the calls even when the phone is locked. Like whatsapp video call where you can answer your calls when the phone is locked.
replyContent: Thank you for the review, and thank you for the suggestion! We will try to implement this feature in the future to improve the ease of picking up a call.

content: Today is the 3rd time I tried to answer a call and the app freezes and says couldn't connect to mic. Seem like they need to update their app functions.
replyContent: Hi We are so sorry that you have been experiencing this! Could you please send us some more information at info@bemyeyes.com so that we can try to fix the issue. Thank you!

content: I would love to help but even with full bars of service, the calls won't come through. I've missed many calls due to this.
replyContent: Hi, we are sorry you have been experiencing issues. Connection errors can be caused by many different issues, but just so we can fix the problem can you please send us more information at info@bemyeyes.com. Thank you!

content: I am a volunteer and this is a great app. I would suggest to allow the volunteers to add more languages because some are bilingual.
replyContent: Hi thank you so much for signing up as a volunteer! You can always add other languages you are fluent in by going to your settings and adding languages under "Other languages." I hope this helps and thanks once again!

content: I heard about this app from my wife and immediately downloaded it. I have only received 2 calls and they made my day. Makes me feel like I am actually putting good back into the world. Definitely recommend.
I just received a call today and the experience wasn't a good one. I felt bad I couldn't help out the lady. The sound wasn't clear and the call ended without me finishing up with her.
replyContent: Hi, we're sorry to hear that and we would love to take a look at the issue. Please reach out to our customer support team at info@bemyeyes.com.

content: I've had several calls, and the only problem I've had so far, is that it doesn't answer immediately. As a matter of fact, it's very slow to answer. It needs a quicker connection.
replyContent: Hey, thanks for writing a review. Sometimes, the app may be slow but such instances are rare. If it happens too often, please let us know at info@bemyeyes.com. We'll have things investigated.

content: We need more app like this! Super easy to use and makes me happy I'm able to help others who are visually impaired.

As a volunteer I love this app. I have some disabilities that are not sight related so know what's it's like to be limited sometimes. Being unable to work this app helps me 'give back' a little. It's nice to be the one helping someone else for a change and I don't even need to be able to get out of bed. It means no matter how unwell I feel I can do something good :) So far the app has run smoothly - it's functional.
I just received my first call and What a wonderful experience helping someone what they were looking for !
The best app I've used in years. What could be better than sharing your sight with someone in need?
Such a brilliant idea. I'm based in the UK, it has worked well the times I have received calls.
I installed this in 2017. It is now 2022. I have never been called. I'm uninstalling it as it's just a waste of space at this point.
Watching a movie called "See for me" and there's just an app like this one used in the movie. I decided to see if something like that exist and thank God it did!
Its an amazing application. I advise everybody to install to help blind people around world.
Installed for about a year now and have gotten calls to help out 3 blind people. An awesome feeling.
Don't ever get any calls and if I do try to answer it, it says the call went to someone else.

This app has potential but there are a few issue. Biggest being the notification system. This app should have a full screen call notification instead of just a pop up. The only reason I knew when I had a call, that I always was to late for, wasbecause I recognised the logo on my always display. Otherwise I would have never known. Fix that and this app can be great.
With so many volunteers I want sure if I would get any calls but I have had 2 so far. Call quality has been great both times

The idea is amazing. However changes need to be made so it doesn't become just another forgotten app. I have been a member for over a month and nothing, so either blind people aren't using it or the filter are not well planned out. There should be a way of putting more than one language which would help increasing chances of getting calls for those who speak more than one language. I strongly believe in the whole idea for this app but changes and maybe a better publicity for it in the blind community should be made so that it can truly bring a great experience to all it's users

Awesome app! If you are looking at this review to see if this app is good, it's not good... It's amazing if you're looking to be a volunteer like myself, Thank You for helping people who don't have the best sight or who can't even see, they just need help with the simplest things and for you to help just for a couple minutes or even seconds YOU help someone around the world. So whoever is looking to be a volunteer try this app!
This morning I helped a person identify and change settings on their heater. I always feel good when I can help another person! -Cara Kaiser
I got two call but when I try to recieve call app doesn't work and there is no option to call back
I have had the app for 10 months and only received 1 call. 🙁 2 years later and not 1 call ☹️.
truly the greatest experience. I think this app is incredible. whoever thought of this is a total genius 👏🏼

Just had my first call. It went amazing, helped a man find what he was looking for. Got to know he's a car guy and he also helped me and listened to my car run and helped me fix the problem! Amazing what humanity can do when we come together to help one another! ❤
I've gotten a few calls, and each time it didn't work. It kept buffering, saying, "Trying to answer your call."
replyContent: Hi thanks for volunteering, and so sorry to hear about this inconvenience. Could you please send us an email with more information at info@bemyeyes.com so that we can address the problem and try to fix it? Thank you so much!

content: Easy to set up, clear communication

What a great idea for an app. One recommendation I have is to have a setting for helpers so they can set their availability to answer calls, just incase some people work backshifts, that way they can still help but there isn't the risk of this app ringing for them if they forget to silence or Do Not Disturb mode their phone!

I haven't helped anyone yet. Perhaps its because of the call takes ages loading before it could connect to the one who is making the call. Needs some bug fixes here. Otherwise, appreciate this initiative.

I have had this app for years and have only got maybe 2 calls the while time. They have to many people helping so you probably will never receive a call. I would try a different app if you truly want to help out the community.

I love the idea of this, I got my first call helping someone today but was very disappointed to see that the camera wouldn't connect so I couldn't help him. I feel terrible and I'm hoping this will help the creators of the app fix this. The screen said it was connecting, I could talk to the man, but I could not see anything. Bless his heart, he was the sweetest man, I feel awful for not being able to help him.

Nice idea, but no availability option. Not risking a call waking me up so will be uninstalling. Would be far better to have times available. Even something like from 0800 to 2000 available, & be able to list your time zone.
replyContent: Hi thank you for volunteering! We actually only send calls to users during the day, and this is done automatically through your device's set time. I hope this helps!

content: Hopefully can be fixed. I tried answering a call this morning and it was unable to connect. I was looking forward to helping someone. I had full bars, I'm unsure if something else is needed
replyContent: Hi! Sometimes there is weak connection on the side of the caller as well, but if the problem happens again please let us know at info@bemyeyes.com so that we can fix the issue. Thank you for volunteering!

content: What a fantastic idea. Volunteered today. My elderly father is blind and hard of hearing. I am his carer but can't always be there. Bought him a smartphone today and will be installing this app on his new phone shortly. I'm hoping to use video calls to help him personally. Still got to teach him how use his phone. What goes around comes around, so willing to be of service to others.
I like the idea, but there really should be an option for volunteers to select their availability for calls. Unfortunately I have to pass on being a volunteer until this is fixed.

I love the idea of this and im eager to help but every single call that has come to me it just spins and says trying to connect call. Must be so frustrating for the person on the other end that needs help
Today was the second call that I have gotten recently that doesn't connect. This application has worked in the pasta. Please fix for those in need of help!
Out of 6 calls i recieved only one was able to connect. The other 5 kept "trying to connect". Very frustrating
replyContent: Hi, thank you so much for being ready to help on six calls. We are so sorry that you experienced connectivity issues so many times. Could you send details of what you are experiencing to our tech support team at info@bemyeyes.com? We'll try to fix the issue. Thank you for volunteering once again!

content: My first call after signing up over 6 months ago, and it just got stuck at the trying to answer call screen. (For well over 5 minutes, I wasn't just being impatient)
Needed to turn on the callers flashlight to read a temperature for them, but the lovely lady caller told me to do this , so with her help I was able to help her out. Nice app.

Devs, are you still there? PLEASE, PLEASE UPDATE THIS APP. I am no longer able to successfully answer Be My Eyes calls and it is heartbreaking to struggle to communicate helpfully and safely to the user on the other end. PLEASE FIX THE APP!!!!
I can answer the call and talk but my phone indicates it's still trying to answer the call... Have not been able to help one person so far... Very disappointed
Won't connect the call. I can talk to whoever calls but the video won't load. Super disappointing. Wish I could help.
replyContent: Hi, usually this is due to a connection issue from either you or the caller. It should be better next time, but if it happens again please let us know with more information at info@bemyeyes.com so that we can fix the issue. Thank you!

content: Was so excited for this opportunity and like the other reviews say, it won't connect. I could hear, but not see anything. I am so disappointed and sad. I am going to uninstall anf come back in a month or so and hope it is fixed.
I had my first call this morning. Perfect connection, no lag. I helped someone find the sliced Jalapeños in their fridge. Quick and easy and humbling.
Good idea but I've never successfully answered a call. I've had 2 calls come through but the app freezes when I hit answer.
Great way to give a hand to others who could have issues with some type of a disability they are experiencing. Recommended for all.

Twice I've installed this app. Both times it has sat on my phone for about five/six months and 've not had a single call. There is obviously no demand for this. Great idea though. Removed it again now to free up space for other apps.
I helped someone identify medication and it was a wonderful experience!

Excellent idea, terrible implementation. This app makes more connection attempts than probably the 10 random apps combined. Even before doing anything with it, and without running it, it's CONSTANTLY trying to contact Facebook & Google & who knows what else. It has 6 trackers encoded , so it seems it just clickbait for people who want to help others, instead of helping they mine your data.uninstall it and be vigilant.Privacy allways matters.

It's a brilliant concept, but appears to be suffering from technical glitches. I only had two calls so far, but one of them wouldn't connect properly. Also, it would be much better if you could set different times for availability. I'm a night owl and would quite happily take calls after 9pm, but not in the morning. An option to add more than one language would be great, as well. I'm bilingual, but there is no way of adding a second language. Apart from that, I think it's great!
The concept is amazing, tried to answer a call today but it didn't pass the trying to answer the call screen. Please fix
It would be good if there was an option to select the hours that you are available to answer. Half the time I miss calls because I'm in the middle of something.
Only issue I have and it may be my mobile data is when I'm out and the video won't load. Other than that great app

Why Cant I set a time up for when people call through. My phone was getting a call from the app at 3 in the morning and to be honest I don't want to be woken up even if it is to help someone. Let someone else who is awake answer the call. Anyway I need to put settings on this I can't see how and don't want to be woken up in the middle of night. Thanks great idea though
replyContent: Hello, sorry you had this experience. Yet, we match based on language and time zone - meaning we only contact volunteers during their daytime hours.  The standard settings only allow you to receive calls between 8am and 9pm (08:00-21:00) in your local time zone by default. You can contact us at info@bemyeyes.com if you need further assistance.

content: I LOVE this app in concept. But both calls I've had in several months, there were technical uses. 😕 Once, the video wouldn't work, so I couldn't help them. The second time, the call dropped. I also wasnt able to help. There's no way to reconnect with them, and i don't know how to get help from the developer, to figure out if there's something wrong with my app.
I've had this about a year and have received 3 calls to help was only able to awnser 2. App will not load if your you tap the icon tho
Question not a review : just installed... Is this app safe in terms of data collection, privacy etc ?

So far received 4 calls but managed to help out 2 due to unfamiliar with the ring tone. Recent help was able to use the flash light tools to light up the environment and see clearly the surrounding. Just hope the flash light will turn off after the call ends, if not, it sure will drain the phone battery.

Awesome service! I tried this out with my blind friend. She was thrilled how easy it was to use from her smart phone, wirh "voice over" comnands. I had someone read fine print on a cleaning product (I couldn't read it, even wirh my glasses), my blind friend got help telling the difference between two similar shaped travel-sive squeeze bottles of toiletries. We were both very impressed!
While this app is great when it works, I have been unable to answer multiple calls as the answer button doesn't work.

Sounds like a good app. I was hoping to help people who are not able to see. Had the app for 3 months, had 2 calls come in and as soon as I accepted the video disconnected. Maybe too many volunteers but the app is taking space on my phone. Really of no use to me if the video calls disconnect as soon as I try to accept. Deleted the app. Good luck to the rest of you. Maybe you'll have better luck.
replyContent: Hello Richard, thank you for the support. You are right, with more than 3 million volunteers, it takes time to get a call. You can help spread the word about Be My Eyes or accessibility in your local community, so we can welcome more blind and low-vision users!

content: Probably the best app on my phone. Have had this app for a few months and only been contacted 3 times. But, what a rewarding experience. On one call I helped a man set the temp on his thermostat. Quick and easy. It must be a god send for those who are visually impaired.

What a beautiful app. Not sure how else to put it. It's an amazing feeling to help someone in need, big or small. I got my first call after 1 day and the gentleman needed help sorting some bills that he had gotten out of sort. It was a pretty quick call, you can tell they're needing help. They need something from you and you get something in return - that great feeling of connecting & helping. The app works great, very simple to use and that's it.
Can't answer calls, even with all the permissions granted. The app keeps shutting down.

Neat experience getting to give assistance to someone in this unique way. Both my calls have been very pleasant. Video quality could have been better, then again I have spotty internet service sometimes, as could the other person. Only downside is you may wait months between calls, but regardless I look forward to them!

Getting a call is really satisfying, but with the one I have had so far the video never started. I was able to use the snapshot tool to get around that but the video was black with a "connecting call" message spinning on top.

When I downloaded this app years ago, it worked great. But in the last few months I've received 2 calls. One could not connect to video and one couldn't answer the call. Feel frustrated on behalf of the blind. Please fix.

App used to work. Now call shows it's trying to connect but never connects fully and shows same circular arrow indicating a connection attempt but it never moves and never connects. Definitely need to invest more in Android app if they actually want to have a global presence.

Just tried to help someone and the video connection could not be established. Heard them just fine but couldn't do anything else. Felt really bad I couldn't help them. I have full bar strength signal.

I dl'd this app ~1-2 years ago (I don't remember how long it's been, now..). So far, I've had a few different people call me, and I've enjoyed a quick and pleasant conversation helping people who are blind to read what instructions are being displayed on their computers, or on some other random item or situation where there's no braille/audio available for them. Every time I helped them quickly and easily; and, was left feeling a sense of fulfillment. Get this app and feel good about yourself!

I really love the concept of this app. However, the last couple of times I've gotten a call, the screen was blank and said "Connecting" even though I could hear the person, and so I was unable to help them. :(

I haven't gotten a call yet, but I really like the idea. One suggestion, adding a days or time preference option to receive calls. I work 12 hour shifts Mon-Thurs and I'm not able to answer the phone. I know that a call would be redirected to someone else if I don't pick up, but that's a waste of the caller's time. If I could set it to only get calls Fri-Sun that would be great.

I received my first call as a volunteer for Be My Eyes yesterday after having the ap installed for several months. The ap is very simple and I was able to answer and assist the person with their task, reading labels. The biggest thing to improve this ap would be more people using it, especially those who are visually impaired, so that it can help more people.

Doesn't allow you to answer from locked phone (Moto g7), unlike normal calls. I've missed 3 calls in the year that I've had this installed, simply because nothing at all shows on screen, just my usual black locked screen, despite ringing. I have to unlock my phone using the pin...which takes time, and by then I've missed it. Really disappointing

I got my first call today but missed it because my phone (almost always kept on vibrate) didn't vibrate. I just happened to look at the screen at the last second. Does your ringer have to be on, or do you have to be staring at your screen when a call comes in? I would love an option to allow vibrate notifications so I have a better chance of responding to a call.

The app is awesome. It connects the vision impaired with a volunteer that can help with everyday tasks as simple as reading a return address on an envelope to choosing between which can is the tomato soup. Whatever the need it is an amazing way for people to help people.

I want to use the shop because I have vision difficulties but I'm not able to log in or complete the process because I can't read the screen so don't you understand that so make it easier for people with limited vision to download the app and execute a sign in otherwise it's useless to me and I have to get another person and that is very very difficult
It's totally fine the stories are mice however if there is a week Wi-Fi connection from the client that needs the volunteer it does become which can make their volunteer feel inadequate
