The idea is cool, but there are technical issues, the most important one is that the feedback does not work. Same as contact us, and at the end of call I was supposed totell how my call was, but the app crushed. This guy that called me is not even blind and just wanted to gather information from me. There is even no way to report these people.
I've been called maybe three times but each time the call did not connect. I was really looking forward to participating.
replyContent: Hi, we apologize for any issue you might be having! Could you send details of what you are experiencing to our customer support at info@bemyeyes.com? We'll get you up and running.

content: The very first screen asks you too agree to the privacy policy and terms of service, but it wouldn't let me click any links to read these, the only button in the screen was "I agree". But how can I agree without even being given the options l to read it.

This is an update on my review, Until now I have only received one call that was the one which dropped... since then nothing. :( I just received a call from someone who most likely needed help but when I answered the call it didn't connect, and the call dropped. I have had the application installed for a while now... this was my first call. I really want to help... the 3 stars is for your great initiative... when I successful help someone using it I will increase your rating.
Always says trying to answer the call and never answers! Very frustrating when u want to help a person that's asking for help
replyContent: Hi, this doesn't sound right, and we apologize for the frustration. Could you please send us an email at info@bemyeyes.com with more information so we can try to fix the issue? Thank you!

content: Got my first call today! Was a very good experience, someone needed help reading labels. Only reason not 5 stars is because the video lagged badly, which made it take more time to read for the person. Had a good connection with audio, and was connected via wifi, so not sure what the vid issue was
I downloaded the app a few months ago, couldn't take the first call i got immediately so i missed that. Today, I finally got to help someone identify currencies. I feel so good about that.

Love the concept & would love to help but I had this installed for 6 mo. , nothing happened. I shared the app with around 100 people inc. those who are visually impaired. They never used it either. Consider advertising to those that need it. I know this may cost $$ & time but if you want this great concept to work, people have to use it. It'd be easy to email the States Schools for the Blind, Social Media groups for the blind, etc. Other reviewers had the same problem. I'll get a list if needed
replyContent: Hello Kea, thank you for the support! It might take some time to get a call. We do reach out to blind organisations regularly and always try to reach out to more blind and low vision users locally. You are more than welcome to spread the word about Be My Eyes in your local community, so we can welcome more blind and low-vision users!

content: I love helping people on this app, wish I got more calls!! You have to answer super quick when you get a call or it understandably goes to the next person! It worked great both times I answered the call in time to help.
What a great idea. The one time I got a call and was able to pick it up on time it did work well so I'd recommend this app to others.
I love helping people ! Who ever invented this app is an angel 😇 got my first call today and I only downloaded the app 2 days ago. Didn't expect it but it was a delight to help 🙂

Love it, but app is buggy. I've gotten 4 calls so far, and was only able to help with the first one. The remaining calls were not able to be opened because the app isn't working. Please fix it soon, I'd love to keep contributing!

Great idea, but the app gave me issues when I got a call today. Lost connectivity, couldn't leave feedback after the call, & the audio came through the regular phone, no option for speakerphone. I hope they improve this. Otherwise, it's so cool!

I was kinda excited to download this because it shows how modern phones are beyond a gaming asset. I suppose the only negative thing I can say about it is that the number of volunteers is so high I will probably never get a call of my own to handle. It's at 187k/3.2m right now. ... Ok, two negative things: the tutorial video is crazy loud. If you're reading this, turn the volume down by like 50%.

Great concept for an app, I'm so happy! Would be great to have more features in the future to interact with the other person in the call, like maps (One time a guy needed guidance to go to a bus station and I found it hard to help as I didn't know where we where) or a chat box to send links (Another guy needed some help with setting a screen reader in his phone and details to contact 'La Once' (National Organization of Spanish blind people) 😊
Got my first call today and it would not let me accept the call after 10 times trying to accept but it did let me decline ... Needs to be fixed asap how can I help when I can answer. 11/13/21

I am a sighted person and was so excited to receive my first call today! The audio was clear and torch (flashlight) controls worked wonderfully. However the video would frequently freeze making it difficult for me to aid the caller. Overall brilliant concept and great app

Excellent idea and so good for not just the caller but the volunteer too. In terms of feelings of fullfillment and usefulness etc certainly but also one of being connected to someone else in times of loneliness etc.. or just wanting to connect. I'm not suggesting people use the platform as a samaritans line but i guess were yet to see where it goes from here. Quite exciting. Especially waiting for my 1st call. Thankyou for the chance to try and be a "growgiver"as Anthony Robins rightly puts it.
Got my first call today but screen just kept saying trying to connect call so couldn't help sweet lady with what she needed. Kind of upset me. 1st call and I've been ok here since 2019. Bummer.
replyContent: Thank you for volunteering, and so sorry that you have experienced issues. We want to take a closer look at this for you. Please send a note to info@bemyeyes.com so we can connect and try to fix the issue.

content: What a beautiful way to be kind and help people in need! I love this app!

Great asset for visually impaired people! (From what I've heard; I'm a volunteer). Very simple and easy to understand and use for a sighted person/volunteer! (I can't say how it is being blind on the app versus being a volunteer, but the community stories that I've read are really positive).

I had my first call today and it went great because I was able to help someone with their bank deposit specially after a person behind them was trying to tell them lies about the information on two checks they were depositing. I was not shown any private information but I was able to tell her what she needed and I'm so thankful that I was able to help!!!!!
When a call came through, I could hear but couldn't see the person I was to help. For some reaaon, the screen was stuck on 'trying to answer call'. You should look into improving the app.
I simply like the idea. Thank you team
I love this app to pieces i use it a lot thank you for making this app for the blind community
Is this app free or does it cost monthly. I really just started this app so I really can't wait right now so I'll give you a three

Hi! I would really love for the app to have a report button of some sort. I just got a call of help from the app unfortunately the person calling us showing his private part to me. I feel like such person should not be allowed to continue to be in that app as for no other people to fall his victim. Hopefully you can consider this idea.
Recently when trying to answer calls it continuously loads and does not answer. Please fix this.

I hope someone's sees this I've been using the app for a little while and only had 1 call so far but the call I had did have some issues with connecting our cameras it just stayed loading and when I tried to send feedback through the app It uses the send feedback option as a share button like I'm trying to send the feedback to and app or other or contacts on my phone. I have a Galaxy Note 10.

It depending on the internet connection, i am a visually impaired, i just wanted to get some help which can be done by 1 call but because with the poor video and audio i needed to make a few calls and it has limit on making calls. Overall volunteers are nice.

Had the chance to answer a call today, and felt so rewarding to be able help someone even in just little ways. At first the connection was kinda laggy but eventually it went well. Was able to help someone even if it's just online. Hope you keep up this good work and so far had no other issues with the app.
Great app (as a volunteer) and it's rewarding when you actually get assist with help requests.

I answered a Chinese speaker's call today but the other end never heard my voice for unknown reason. The video call then stop working as it freezes at one point and became black screen. I just hope that the person got the help they needed, maybe it's a bug to do with this app, but I hope not.

I've only answered one call. It was very simple. A package to the wrong house, they wanted help reading the name. Took less than 5 minutes. The visual quality of the video was disappointing. Since that's the most important part, it was not easy to read lines of text coming through but we got it done. Better video quality is a must.

I want to give this app 5 stars. But the first call I was able to answer, the person needed my help reading a document in a language I didn't know! I felt awful because I wanted to help and couldn't. I thought my settings were set up for English, and when I went to double check, it just sits on a "Please wait..." Screen. Please continue to refine this app to make sure we can help more folks.

I personally relate to the mission of this app and seeing so many people lend their time in search of helping the visually impaired is heart warming and if you're even thinking of downloading this app to help even just in your spare time, please do. It makes a world of difference.

Update: I have picked up a call without any problem!Thank you! I'm giving the app 5stats now! I have received three calls in a row just for today but everytime I pick up, a dialog box will pop up saying "An error occured and the call has ended". I wonder if there's something we can do to fix this. But still, kudos to the developers! Such a great app for those in need and those who wants to help them!
What a brilliant idea! Cant wait to use it or to be of help to others. Thank you for creating a way to give help freely and easily....
No option to select multiple languages for multilingual people. Limits scope of help.
replyContent: Thank you for downloading the app and for leaving feedback! If you go into "Settings" you can add more than one language under "Other languages." While you will largely receive calls in your "Primary Language," the app does allow you to receive calls in any language you are fluent in. I hope this helps, and thanks again for volunteering!

content: Just completed my first call. Everything worked fine, and being able to help people is great.

I so far haven't helped anyone, but I'm excited to help someone in the future and the concept is just great! I was blessed with no colour blindness or any blindness but this is such a nice and easy way to help people! Great concept, great app! Get it, doesn't cost you a cent and you can help others!!

I'm a low vision therapist and found this app because 2 total blind patients were scheduled so I wanted to be prepared to provide more than what is available for patients with low vision. I tried it, a volunteer quickly answered. We were both new to using the app but she was a great help to me. I will know how to guide all of my patients on how to use and what to expect. Thanks to all the volunteers and to the developer. I'll spread the word very quickly about this app.

so I've had this app on my phone for about 3 years and I have NEVER received a call. I'm one of those horrible people that always has my phone in my hand so I figured this is great. Except that whatever algorithm this app uses doesn't work right. My coworker downloaded the app and got over 10 calls in less than 4 months. I love the concept but you need to fix the call distribution system.
replyContent: Hello Alyssa, we apologise for your experience. Your coworker seems lucky, and must be rated positively by the users, because it might take some time to get calls among 3+ million volunteers. Thank you for the feedback!

content: installed this app in July last year...tonight I got my first call! super user friendly and it's silly but to finally get a call and help someone was super rewarding. took 3 minutes or so out of my night. wish I could help more but i love that this service is there for the blind and visually impaired

I think that the app is a great concept, when it works. I've only been able to answer one call and the call was super grainy. I could not help like I needed to. I had a call that I could not answer at all. The app froze as I was trying to send feedback on a recent call and when it finally started up again it chose the call experience was good and it was not. If the bugs can be fixed, it'd be a great app!!

An amazing app that lets sighted people help visually impaired people do the things we take for granted. I've only received one call but it was a great feeling to be able to help her get the right frozen meal out of the freezer area. Do it! Get the app!

So i joined up cause i wanted to help and this was a neat idea... my very first call, it was some guy masterbating in what looked like a child's room...i clicked off it so fast that the end call/ rate the experience button i clicked off trying to get out of the call and the app has no contact info/ customer service to really report the phone call after the inital end screen. A lot of people are going to end up abusing this service which is a shame.
replyContent:
Hi Stephanie, 

we are extremely sorry that you have experienced inappropriate behaviour in the Be My Eyes app! We do not tolerate abuse. At the end of every call, you have the possibility to report an abuse directly to us. We then proceed to block the reported user forever. 

You can also contact us at info@bemyeyes.com

content: Great app. let's us contribute in making the world little more accessible for the visually impaired. A great tool to increase the bonding between those who can see the world with their eyes and those who can not. A great way to bridge the divide and help create a collaborative world. Hope, people come out with more and more innovative apps like these to help those with challenges. Kudos and best luck..!!!

Issue with the calls. While the concept is great, I have received 4 calls so far and I was unable to answer any of them. The buttons on the screen were not working whatsoever! I really want to be able to help but it's pointless for me to keep this app if I can't use it :(

I think thats a really very good initiative for the people who are blind and its also very great app for the people who are willing to help them as this type of little change can bring something great and as i can see that there are more people who want to help then the one who needs help which clearly determine that there is humanity alive somewhere. Wonderful creaters hats off.👏🏻

Great app, loved the idea. One suggestion if I may; add an ON/OFF option at the app's home screen where I can activate receiving a help request, as I might be in a meeting, asleep or even low on GSM data where I can't accept calls, by this everyone can activate the app whenever they are ready to lend a hand and by this saving time for the requesting part not to wait longer for the app directing the call to others if the first didn't answer.

Beautiful! I love the idea of this app and was just thinking something like this needs to exist for those trying to travel on our horrendous trains services and even airports, when this app was mentioned on the programme I was watching! My only concern about this being an open community app is that it leaves open for trolls. My suggestion to make it more secure would be to register a face photo and Passport page to ensure people are genuine and can be traced if they abuse this system or people.

I just answered my first call and it was amazing! This app is very easy to use and when a call came through, it connected quick with decent resolution. This app really does help with the little things that those with vision take advantage of.

I wanted a magnifier. This would not let me use the magnifier without signing up to a volunteer scheme to help the blind. This is a good thing but I'm not signing up to an open ended commitment just to get a magnifier. If there had been more info on the commitment or another option I might not have uninstalled it before even using it.

Sound doesn't work. I got one call and it hung up immediately. Sending feedback doesn't work - WhatsApp was trying to send something (not sure what) and it asked me for a contact, instead of having the contact pre-filled and letting me write the content. Xiaomi Mi 10 Lite.

I downloaded this app with the intent to help blind people and the visually impaired. when reading through the terms of use, I found out that they will have the right to use and monetize anyting you create on this app including whatever is said and recorded over video. I do not like videos of me being used and monitored without my consent, so I ended up deleting the app. Please add a choice to not grant access to the content, as I really want to help the impaired.
replyContent: Hello, we need to record videos for safety and security concerns. Yet, a very selected number of people from our team have access to those videos. No video will ever be used or be published for any reason and on any platform without your consent.

content: This is a great app in concept but I've been a member for months now without a single call. It's basically a useless app sitting on my phone taking up space. There should be an option to choose availability as well. I work nights so I could be available says and nights on certain days. I'll keep the app for a little longer but if I get over 6 months with no use I'm deleting. EDIT 1/29/20 It has been over a year now with no call. Useless and takes up space.
replyContent: Hello, since we have 3+ million volunteers, it might take time to get a call. All we can ask for is your patience, we hope you will catch a call quite soon. In the meantime you can help spread the word about Be My Eyes in your local community, so we can welcome more blind and low-vision users!

content: Got my first call today. First time for me and the person I was helping. Audio was good and picture was sharp. I was able to help, exchange pleasantries and finish the interaction in just a couple of minutes. It was a good feeling to help someone, plus it was so easy.

I logged in with my Google account very easily and was able to make my first call within a minute. The volunteer was a real person and was able to assist me with answering the question I had. There were some issues with audio. If you log in and choose to be a volunteer first then it might not do this but I selected to test the need assistance option first, and now it will not let me choose to be a volunteer?

Its an amazing app, i however have 1 concern, i sorta have phone anxiety, a call made my heart beat fast, and i did a call testing. The loud beeping/ vibrating sent me in a bit of a panic. If possible please let us have the options to make it less vibrating, or possibly just a little tiny ping. Thank you

I love the concept of the app but I have a doubt that if I get a call in night it will just wake me up. So please add a feature in which you can select the time that you will be available in and can help another visualy impaired person.

Great idea but just collecting dust. I had the app about a month without getting any notifications or calls I love the idea of this but maybe there is a app issue or more than enough have signed up and it over crowded with people who want to help but that's not a bad thing if that's the casr

Great initiative but app is not. I never get video connected so it doesn't serve the purpose. I had to ask callers twice that they need to call again as I have connectivity issues. Feedback button also does not work so I'm providing my feedback here.

Hiya Went to send a suggestion but it only directs you to share the app. Thought I'd write it here. I think it would be great to have an option of more than one language for people who are bilingual + That's all. Otherwise a brilliant app and brilliant idea

This app is a great concept however when I first started using it I could get videos from ppl I was helping. Now all I get is still shot pics. It makes it a little more difficult to help out. I wish you all would fix this asap!!

Hey, this to give a tiny winy suggestion. Many people are bilingual,let alone multi-lingual. If the app can have an option of choosing more than 1 language, it'll make reaching out for the people in need more feasible.

Would love to hear from support as I had a technical issue with a call and at the end I could only thumbs up the call rather than report the issue and when I went to press "send us feedback" in the actual app it won't click when every other button works.

If u don't give five stars to this app, you can't give 5 stars to any other app. It's helping a lot of people. It's an amazing feeling to help someone in need. Thank you so much "Be my eyes" team of developers. 🤗 Btw there is a minor connection problem when internet speed is a little low. Please fix that.

A great idea, but poor follow up. I have had this app for over a year now, I have received total of 2 calls. It is a shame that there is such an imbalance between the number of volunteers and visually impaired people. This app could change the world for a lot of people from especially less developed countries, including my own. I find it difficult to understand how the same people who had the idea to create such an amazing app, does absolutely nothing to improve their app and awareness... SHAME

Signed up yesterday evening after my daughter told me about the app..just had my 1st call, less than 24 hrs later. What an awesome experience, even if it was just telling them what color something was. It pleases me to be able to help just that little bit more in my free time. Amazing, good job creating this! Something so simple helps so much :)

wonderful idea! can you make another version of this app called "be my ears"? I, personally, have had hearing issues for a long time and think this would help people who are hearing impaired as much as it has helped people who are visually impaired. Keep up the good work!

When the Android version of this finally appeared, I was excited to have a chance to help vision-impaired people in such an ingenious way. (It also seemed to make sense for the developers to stop focusing exclusively on Apple owners—who are, in my experience, more likely to be preoccupied with style and status than "the rest of us" are.) However, after having it installed for months, and not getting a single help request, I'm giving up. I'm glad the volunteer response has been so overwhelming—better that than too few—but there's also something to be said for, you know, actually getting to help someone sometime..?
I think this app is brilliant. I have had one opportunity to assist so far . But I have missed so many. The app needs a distinct loud ring tone. It is so quiet on my phone I often miss the alert.

I've had this app for many months and just got my first phone call today. I helped a lady identify dollar denominations. It feels good to be able to assist people. It's too bad I don't get the opportunity to assist more often, but looking at the number of volunteers compared to the number of blind users it makes sense.

Had a call once that i couldn't even answer, other than that it was just spam notifications of "inspirational stories" from the developers. then suddenly it wasn't installed anymore. Great idea. have no idea if it actually helps anyone.
replyContent: Hello Chris, thank you for your nice words! Since we have 3+ million volunteers, it might take time to get a call. All we can ask for is your patience, we hope you will catch a call quite soon. In the meantime you can help spread the word about Be My Eyes in your local community, so we can welcome more blind and low-vision users.

content: The app works really well and is a good way to help people. I've only ever gotten one call but that's very understandable as according to the count in the app there are 3 million volunteers and only around two hundred thousand blind people using it so it makes sense that calls would be rare

Thank you for adding still image option - I did not use it this time as gentleman did not ask for much detail. If he needed more information, this feature would have been especially helpful. I sincerely appreciate the opportunities to be of service - such a beautiful thing!

I just downloaded this app and I'm so so exited to start helping out. I am bilingual and happy to help in both English and Spanish languages, however, the app only allows me to choose one language. If there's a way to select more than 1 language would be great.

I love the concept a lot but I have a problem I got two calls on March 8th the day I signed up but I haven't gotten a call since currently It's July 22 and I don't think this is even fixable but it was the only reason I'm giving it four stars Update: I got a call today! I was able to help someone find clorox wipes. I'm so glad this app exists.

I am new to this app, and I think that a good improvment could be the possibility of helping in two or more different lenguages, fir example, I speal both spanish and english fluently, and I can only choose one to help, so yeah, that could be a good update to this fantastic app

I am so glad this service exists, and have been anxiously awaiting my first call. When it rang, I clicked the button to connect but it would never connect. I felt terrible because I knew someone on the other end of the line needed help and I was unable to provide assistance. I hope they were able to connect with another volunteer.

I took my first call today, after two months of downloading the app. It was a lady from England and I got very exited! The camera quality wasn't the best, but we managed to have a good interaction. She needed me to check on expiration dates for some cookies. It was an undescribable feeling that I felt after the call was over. I love this app and would like to help more people.

feedback: had my first call and it was really exciting! 2 improvements. 1) when the call comes in, it should indicate the language you should speak in. i have mine set as multilingual, and the individual who called did not speak my default language in English. awkward at first. 2) how can you set the phone call to silent if youre in a meeting? i would like to mute it but not my entire phone.

As with other recent reviewers, wonderful concept with subpar execution on my phone (Pixel 4a). Maybe there's a bug that's currently causing so many calls to be fail to connect. Feels horrible to get so excited to help someone only to have to tell them you can't see their video and can't help them. Would love to give a 5 star review if the bug is fixed!

such a great app. im a colorblind makeup artist and sometimes I need help telling deep colors apart. when I call theres always someone there to help me sort it out. I dont have to look inept and ask people on set. its awesome.

It's a great idea, I haven't answered a call yet, but the only reason I gave 4 stars is because apparently the app has to be open to get calls, at least that's how I saw it works on my phone. I left the app open and I got my first call in the morning (I didn't receive any since I downloaded the app) and while I was at he dentist I couldn't answer at the time. So my guess is that it only works if it's open, would be great if you could fix it.

Simple idea but utter genius! You get an alert, shown a video link to a blind or visually impaired person. You see what they can't and talk to them. Could be which is an item of clothing or expiry date or product ingredients. Easy, simple way to make a small but significant difference to a blind person.
What an amazing use of technology! Super easy to use. Tons of volunteers so the call volume is low but hopefully this app gets more exposure soon so we can help more people who need it!

Just singed up to be a volunteer so I havnt even received my first call to be of help to someone nevertheless, I am so excited to be able to provide such simple yet vital aid to another induvidual in need. Very quick set up that took may be 4 min total, including doing a practice of how to answer a call and watching the very breif video within that practice. We need more apps such as this to better the world around us; and not the thousands of mindless/pointless apps without a shred of purpose

Awesome app for helping people the issue is its rare that you get calls which is both good and sucks. I wish you could toggle something to be ready to receive calls because there's been 2 cases where I've gotten calls at bad times.

Finally got a call today that I was able to accept in time. I could hear and see the person in need of help perfectly, but unfortunately they could not hear me. Not sure if it was an issue with my device, their device or the app itself, however I was a bit disappointed.

Oh God, I could not have anticipated the joy this would be. It works seamless and the app tries pairing up geographically which helps everyone better understand and be able to help each other. The experience itself is often short, but leaves you feeling incredibly wholesome for far longer

Review as a volunteer : I'm happy to be able to help even in the smallest things. As for the app love the option to turn on the flashlight. Easy to use,Very user-friendly. Can help people in multiple languages! Just grateful for this app

What an absolutely amazing idea for an app. Have already made many of my friends and family download this app. And the fact that you rarely get a call (which many people seem to be complaining about) is actually a good thing. It means there are enough volunteers that no one seems burdened by having to take frequent calls, so I urge people not to delete it just because you haven't got a call.

The idea of the app is amazing! I'm Excited to be apart of it. However, I got my first call tonight but it wouldn't answer. It kept saying trying to connect and I felt as though I let whoever was on the other side down. I then tried to open the app but it just kept loading. Bummer. Hopefully next time it'll work.

Love the idea of the app but since you have so many visual volunteers perhaps we can list special skills. For example I'm a Registered Nurse, I would be happy to help explain medication or prescription instructions, our guide someone through doing a bandage change even if a sighted person is present.
I've gotten two calls to help someone visually impaired inthe past 3 years & it has been heart warming & fun both times! I look forward to helping as many people who need it as possible. 🥰

I downloaded this app a year ago and have been lucky enough to have been able to help several people on here. They'll call you through the app, so nobody has your personal info, which is great! It's quick & easy to setup & you can help immediately! You can help whenever someone calls you & if you're busy you can let it go & they'll get connected to someone else because they have over a million volunteers! A great way to give back & help others, ESPECIALLY now with the craziness going on!q

Dont get me wrong, i love the app!, the only reason im giving it 4 stars is because since i work in other non-profit  where your main users are also helping others, you have to create strategies that feed theses users ego, and by that i mean let them know how much they are helping so they can keep coming back for more.   I think the app needs a dashboard where i can see how many calls i answered, how many minutes i spent helping the app main users.  Otherwise is always a great pleasure to help and it´s so satisfying.!

This app is a great idea and perfectly executed. For blind users this is great and there's so much help instantly at your fingertips. No long waits in ques for help just instantly answered. However for volunteers I don't suggest at this time downloading this app at this time because there's 2.5 million volunteers and only 137k blind looking for help. So many people want to help that it could be weeks or months before you get one call.
Just learning and interested in signing up

I downloaded this app months ago, or late last year and have been waiting for a call since then. I got my first call just now but unfortunately I couldn't speak Spanish and the person that needed help only spoke Spanish. I badly wanted to help, and I was so excited to help too. I hope there would be a feature where in they could match the caller to the people who can speak the language. :( really sad I couldn't help and I feel guilty now too. Hoping this would be improved!
I tried to send a feedback but it sent me to the share menu it seems. Also the test call is not working with my bluethooth headset, but it worked on the speakers. Great concept/idea!
It's really work, i've just recived a call and i helped him. Wonderful app for everyone. Much obligated to you guys

I like the idea of the app and I'm glad it's working for the users I have however had this app installed for well over a year now and haven't received a single call. On the one hand it's great and it means there's lots of volunteers, but on the other hand it kinda feels like a waste to keep this app installed hence why I'm deleting it. I hope the app remains helpful to all users, and that they maybe add a way to see your position in q or something I don't really know but just something.

I've only ever gotten one call as a volunteer since downloading this app... I wish there was a way to set available hours because I work split shifts but I'm also a night owl so if someone in another timezone needed help, and I was available even if it was night for me, that would be awesome.

So far I have only assisted 1 person, but I think I got just as much out of the interaction as the person I was assisting. This is innovative and integral to the type of ideas we as a species need champion for the betterment of humanity as a whole. This is the way forward and I hope anyone who reads this will also understand the importance. Thank you to the developers that brought this the world

Haven't got my first call yet but this app gets the best rating from me absolutely possible just on idea. I'm sure the service is great aswell but I cant honestly say yet. We need more people like the creators of this app and more apps the bring love to the world. Thank you so much to whomever had a hand in putting this app on the market. You all truly are heroes!!
It was an awesome experience! I had a little trouble with the focus trying to see the date on a bottle, but then we adjusted on his end and I was able help. it really felt good!

I love the idea. And to be honest, I first learned about Be My Eyes from a blind friend which led me to download the app. I have gotten one call so far. But just now I realized that probably the team can make an option for vibration as notification when someone is calling or even sound when my phone is set to silent mode. Bcs that's what I do to my phone most of the time. Although it does not mean I wouldn't answer if there is a call. I hope my suggestion is understood. Thank you!

I LOVE the concept of this app. However, the last two times I got a call and went to answer it froze. Please fix it. I really love the app and want to be able to answer the calls. The first time worked perfectly, but not the last two.
Disconnects. Needs better optimization

Awesome and such a great way to help... This is such an easy way for you to help your fellow people that need assistance with day to day things. The payback in knowing you were able to help someone by doing something because you have sight and they don't shows how we take things for granted some time. Do us all a favor and help out and volunteer 🙋‍♀️ 🙏 😉
The idea is excellent but why every call come to me when I was sleeping?! It will be better to improve the app with the option of selection the best time for you to receive calls.

What an awesome concept! It just keeps getting better with updates. Now, I want to address the one star reviews. I am really sorry you guys are upset that you haven't gotten a call, but that doesn't make this app "pointless". ugh, it is helping so many non or partially sighted people. If you came to this app hoping you'd get your regular dose of warm and fuzzies off the backs of blind people, you're mistaken. This app was made to help people and it is helping.
i got a call it was awesome experience i felt much better afterwards this made me of help to others and the experience is priceless

I haven't used it yet but I will and I think this is fantastic. I read a few reviews about people not recieving calls for months. I'm leaving this review to see how far you guys have gone on advertising this app directly to the ones who actually need it. Hospitals, retirement homes, homes for the blind should be places to target to expand the audience and customer's in need or people who want to help. A lot of people can get it for their love ones. Keep up the good work though.

I love this app! Ive only had 5 or 6 successful calls in 2 years but with 5mil volunteers thats to be expected. The reason i give 4 instead of 5 stars is because ive received 1 or 2 calls that wouldn't connect for some reason and therefore i couldnt help those people. Other than that i love this app and think its a fantastic way of helping out the blind community- being able to make a small difference to someone's day is nice :)

What a wonderful idea. Just used it for the first time: took no time to connect. Couldn't find the thing I dropped but at least I feel better that if we both couldn't see it, it isn't just me. it's definitely hiding! I wish all health professionals and charities and other organisations knew Be My Eyes, to suggest to people. When I've given a few tries (I'm cautious about recommending to others), then I'll be spreading the word. Just wish I could volunteer. Thank you for this service!
I've had 2 calls and unable to answer both feeling rude unable to help the person on the other end 😥🦄😥 this is not nice

Received my first support call after installed this app for many years! Although the network connectivity was very poor, we managed to build a good teamwork within a few minutes. Feel so happy to be able to help her to find a nearby store to get a mask and get a taxi home. This experience also let me feel deeply how challenging it is without sight. I hope I can be a help for many friends in this community.

Took 8 months to finally get a call but worth it. I helped an elderly lady read the directions on a packet of jello mix. Those 30 seconds made my day. I wish i got calls more often but there are 5 million sighted people ready to help only 300k visually impaired people haha, so no wonder it took 8 months for me to be picked by the app to answer a call
Amazing app. I've been a volunteer since December and I'm enjoying my experience.

(Sighted Volunteer) Awesome assistance with some awesome people. My calls have been few and far between, but they do happen. Super easy to do -- just be yourself, be honest, and don't be afraid to possibly throw in some small talk! I have recommended many friends and family members to join after they have encountered me recieving a call out of nowhere and were mind blown. Try it out!

Great resource. There are so many more volunteers that people who actually need help. Which is fantastic, however, the app is taking space and I've never used it in the month I've had it so I may end up deleting it if I'm not needed. Keep in mind that this just means that they are already receiving help from someone else, which is GREAT. 💕 So happy that there is a resource like this for the blind. 😊
Great idea, terrible execution. App doesn't recognize when it is given permissions.
replyContent: Hi! Thanks for your feedback, could you please send us more info so that we can make the app better? All you have to do is describe your issue to us at info@bemyeyes.com. Thank you!

content: Amazing idea for an app. So helpful. The app just sits on my phone until someone calls. Feels great to be able to help someone with simple things that we take for granted.
I received my first call today and the audio was terrible, it eventually disconnected 😭😭😭😭 and I couldn't help

It worked perfectly with me I had no problem with the other person about internet or call disconnecting, we end up by solving the problem that he had together . I was so happy to talk to him and help . But the problem is that I have never received a call since that day, its been now more than 5 months and Im updating the app and everything but nothing :(

It will be good if you can group based on their expertise. Because we get many requests where the blind will require help with computer operations. If a person who is not an expert answers the call it will be of no news. Even I received a call from a blind lady to help her identify the best matching pant for a top, I am not at all good in such things. So it would be good if only a subset of volunteers with required strengths receive the help request.

Great concept but there needs to be a way of setting available hours. Also it might be nice to have a way to set things like "override my hours if the caller is declaring an emergency" (call urgency). Keep working on it.
Good app for blind people and great achievement and idea 💡

Amazing! The fact that I could help someone I didn't know, so overwhelms me. This has become a permanent fixture on all phones going forward. What a miraculous app. As far as I am concerned, this should be preinstalled on every phone instead of the likes of Facebook.

Love the concept! This app is doing a wonderful service to people in need. I wish I could write a personal review, but after almost a year I've never gotten to use it. Not a bad thing. There just aren't as many needing help as there are volunteers. I'm uninstalling only because I actually forgot I still had this app, and I don't want to get caught off guard if a call ever does come in from it.

I have really enjoyed this app but the last two calls I got it wouldn't ever connect. My app, phone and signal is update and strong. I feel like I've let two folks down now because I couldn't help them.
The idea of this app us great, but the technicality is not. Can't help when it is trying to connect you and fail almost every time. It would be nice if the developers fix this.

obe my eyes is great to have people helping other people with visial challenges, It is great to read stories where someone can help someone else far away instead of being in the ssme room. thank you be my eyes team for having a place to go for help, especially when you need help right now not in a minute.

A simple yet very kind concept, well implemented, providing great opportunities for someone with reasonable eyesight (like me) to help someone who would like and value that assistance. Such is the joy and power of kindness that I feel happier to be able to help in often simple yet appreciated ways; and also to learn from and marvel at the very different perspectives and rich lives of blind and partially sighted people, both through the individual connections and the amazing "podcast" interviews.

I recieved my very first call about a month ago and it was for an elderly lady that wanted to make sure her outfit matched!! I love to be able to help... I wish I got more calls though... I have had this app about a year and only been used that once... still an A+++++ app and idea!!! Maybe you can come up with ansign language interpreter!!!

Stop giving one star or so cause 'there's not enough blind people'. Like, uhm, what? Isn't not being fast enough to be the first one to accept a call a good sign? The app is working just fine and supporting the blind well. I can understand y'all do want to help, but they know best when and how often they need help, don't push them into 'needing' help!
Everytime a call comes through it just loads and loads no one or nothing happens.
Love the concept of this app! To be able to help others is very enjoyable

I very much like this app I just installed it would go and have her see my first phone call today, it was very heartwarming to be able to help the person out, and when I read the other reviews about the app and how it's useless, it kind of pisses me off because people don't realize I don't care enough to read that when a blind person needs help it connects them to ten callers so it's only when they're the first one to pick up they get connected

My first time answering a call and I couldn't hear the person very well and watch the video call at the same time because I wasn't able to play the sound through my speaker phone, had to keep putting the phone to my ear and off again to look at the video call. If there's any way to add a speaker phone option would work out better.

although the concept is amazing there is such a larger ratio of volenteers to users. I have had the app installed for weeks ans today I recieved my first call I jumped at the chance to answer and did just was quickly met with male genitalia less then 10 seconds into the call. I repirted the caller and I recieved a email saying the person had been blocked so they are clearly very pro active but I dont really want it installed any more.
So far, I'm unable to use this. I went to make the test call and there was absolutely no sound, and then all apps in my phone stopped making sound too. Some kind of bug.

I think this is a great app! Although it may be a good idea to add the option to choose whether you receive messages/calls only so people who may experience phone anxiety can also help out as much as possible.

I'm a volunteer on this app and I absolutely adore it. I get a couple of calls a month perhaps from blind people who need help with various daily tasks, such as identifying "use by"-dates on packaging and we always end up having a lovely chat. It's really made me realise how little the world caters to blind people, so I'm now also supporting a charity that trains guide dogs. Highly recommend this app!

I received a call and the caller wanted to know tge uses of the app but his camera wasn't working well and then the call ended suddenly 😕 I was really disappointed I recommend sending the volunteers an idea about the view of the other one when they call.

As volunteers who want to help and users who need help, people should be sharing this app like gossip at a church picnic. With so many volunteers, just about every informational resource available to visually impaired people should include this app. The ratio of volunteers/users is so immense, getting an actual call to action once a year is understandable. I'm going to be in a bit of self denial about the Data-Mining reviews, I'm hoping the trackers are to enhance connectivity.

I am a volunteer - I received a call for the first time today, and I answered, but it never connected with anyone. I wanted to try to find information, maybe I had done something wrong, or maybe I needed to report a bug, but I couldn't find any place to do either thing, either in the app or on the Be My Eyes website. Hopefully whoever called was answered by someone else and not just left hanging? (Still 4 stars because I'm not the one it needs to work for, I'm just a volunteer.)
Whenever I receive a call and I try to answer it never goes through.
It's an honor to be at service, I finally caught a call and man does it bring joy to my heart, ghetto and all we appreciate the opportunity to help whenever possible. God bless
I'm so glad to have found this app. I need another set of eyes.
First call right out of the gate the video didn't connect. Not sure whose side the issue was on but they had to try again. Disappointing and frustrating for both.

This is an amazing and innovative app. If you have the time to spare then you can genuinely make a difference to someone who is sight impaired. You're helping people with everyday tasks, which really makes you appreciate what you have. Beneficial for both parties.

I just got my first call and it was amazing to help someone out. The gentleman who called needed help for their fashion class in college and had me look up a dance video to describe their clothing. This helped him get through his big project and felt great!!! This app is amazing!!!

Amazing idea, and super easy to use. The only downside is that because there are so many volunteers, it might be a while before you get your first call. But answering calls and helping is simple and people are very appreciative.

downloaded the app yesterday and got a call the next day! it was an old man trying to figure out what color 2 of his shirts are. it was a quick one although we did have to figure out how to move the phone camera a bit. i used to work at a call center company so i was very familiar with how to help people in need. this is a good app to help people

It's interesting, but if you don't answer within the first few seconds someone else get it. It's like they send a call to everyone in the app at the same time to answer. Had a guy call me that I'm unsure was visually impaired though, seems like he just wanted to talk to me about my personal relationship with Jesus Christ. Did not appreciate being hijacked by a witness when trying to help people. Other than that it's been cool!

people keep complaining about not getting calls but,,, thats not the point. just wait until you're needed. it doesn't take much storage so its no biggie. i think its a cool app for blind people (hopefully it works well??) and it would take much time to answer a call for someone, so why not?

This app is absolutely amazing! What happens when something comes up that is unexpected? There are countless people here ready to help out at a moments notice! if we can all band together to assist with anything that someone is going through that makes our community stronger and removes any political ties, racial boundaries, etc.. Every human is beautiful and we should rally around our people in times of need 😊
Should add more visula assistant.should advertising more on social media to get audience

Love the app, but several times the video quality is not clear enough to read out the text other person is asking for, so please fix that, or it is an internet issue, sorry but fix it if it's from your end.
I think you guys need to update this app. Got my first call today but the wheel just spun around and said connecting. It never connected. I went and did a test call again, and no sound.
I'm pretty disappointed I wasn't able to help someone who called for help today . After accepting the call I just received a message stating, "trying to connect call." Please fix this issue .

This is a great app. I'm a new volunteer and the man I helped with my first (and only call so far) was extremely grateful I could help him. He said even though the questions and needs may seem small they are a big deal to the blind community. It was also fun to have a short chat with him; someone who lives on the other side of the country from me but quickly didn't feel like a stranger at all.

I've had this app for a month or so, and I've not been able to help anyone. The population of volunteers grows faster than the population of blind people in the app. It'd be nice to see how many blind and volunteers are connected at the same time, to evaluate if there's or not need of having the app running.
Great app, the initiative to help individuals requiring visual assistance is incredible. Gives you an excellent feeling when you can genuinely help someone.

It's awesome how you can help for free in less than a minute. Knowing you can do something to help people in need around the globe is just so awesome. The camera is clear, so are the voices. This is just such a good application. I was so delighted to be able to help and make a difference in blind people's everyday tasks. Thank you so much Be My Eyes team and I really hope everybody downloads this app!
A great app for visually impaired. We can volunteer to help them do small yet challanging day to day activities. Easy to use and more importantly the UI is simple

My experience on this app has been humbling to say the least... I've been able to attend quite a few calls and do my bit to help the ones in need! My congratulations to the team that developed this app! Absolutely brilliant initiative!

5-star concept 1-star app execution Such a great concept but the app sucks. Calls won't connect video, so you have to take manual screenshots every few seconds to try to keep up. Additionally, all "send feedback" options instead trigger "share" actions, so no way in-app to submit feedback. I tried via [settings > share feedback] as well as [stories > share your story > contact us]. This review is specific to the latest Android app on Google Pixel 4XL.
Could talk but screen still was trying to receive call. Had to hang up on the guy. Please fix
replyContent: We apologize for this experience. To better understand the problem you encountered, please contact us at info@bemyeyes.com so we can help resolve this issue. Thank you.

content: I like the idea bof this app but i don't know how can i use it or offer my help for people !
Would be better if I could specify the times I could help out.
The felling of helping someone of the comfort of my house or office is so satisfying

I love the idea of the app and it's really lovely that someone came up with it at all but I've never received a call from anyone needing help and I've had it for just under a year. While I'm glad that there are far more sighted people to help than people who need it, it does mean that I can't give the full 5 stars I want to since I haven't experienced all aspects of the app.
I've answered a couple of calls in a month after months of silence. Very happy to know it works! Both times, I answered a call asking me to help read some setting off a gadget.
Brilliant app. It has been great to offer help to those who need it in in such a modern way.
Unresponsive App - when trying to respond to a call, the app responds with "please wait" and absolutely nothing else happens. Great idea, but not so much if the tech lets it down.

Let's not talk about the Software side! This is a great idea and when you come to think that it's been build completely to benefit someone else in need!!!! Great job! Absolutely loving the app and the idea! Everytime when I get a call my heart gets filled mich happiness!
I really love this idea, but the past three calls I've received the app just wouldn't pick up the call. I accept the call and it freezes up.

I m glad they have such a helpful app for helping the people out! Keep up the great work ! Also , since there are soooo many volunteers, why not create a "REGIONAL" system where the volunteers would be called by blind people's who need help in their country (or even continent). That would give other volunteers more opportunity.

I installed it to help anyone at anytime. Never mind what I'm doing, I would gladly leave anything I'm doing just to help. I'm so happy 😀 to be able to help people— though being far away from each other— it would be amazing to know that by installing this app, you're being of great help to someone. I can't explain how exhilarating ☺️ I'm feeling right now!!! ❤❤❤❤❤

Disclaimer: I do NOT know for sure whether this App is connected to Wangiri fraud (google it up!). But one day after I install this App, I started to receive multiple calls from overseas unknown numbers, mostly from Senegal. Just beware of the possibilities before you use the App. The intention may be good, but the possibility to harm you from bad people exploiting the App's loop holes exists !!!

i have a suggestion: on the homepage add a button for volunteers to turn on and off "availability", so that way if you're not currently available to be called- the caller doesn't waste time trying to call you and it automatically connects them to someone who has their "availability switch" turned on.

Nice app! It would be great if the helper could see beforehand which language the caller is set on, because I usually don't know which language that I have put into the app should I start with and if I speak a foreign language the person on the other side is usually unsure what is going on.

I honestly would love to give this app 5 stars. But the truth is I've installed it and registered for help over 2 years ago and I never received any request of assistance. I set the language as Italian cause that's the language I'm more comfortable with. Kind of disappointed :-/

Great concept but app needs work. I received a call for help today but the video was black and I only could occasionally get a still image to load. It was very frustrating for the caller who needed help

Great app idea! I got a call but I couldn't hear him. He could hear me so I read him all I could see then said maybe he would like to call back for a clearer connection I wasn't sure but I did all I could with what I had. I've been helping blind people all my life as one of the greatest women in my life was blind, my grandmother. Sad I couldn't fully help because of a connection problem.
This app is a really nice idea. One thing that would make it 5 stars is an option to activate/deactivate calls, so I can clock out when busy.
Such a wonderful idea! I've only been able to answer one call so far since they seem to be picked up really fast! But the video quality can be improved slightly. Other than that, a great initiative.
Call wasn't connecting .... please look into this .... 🙏🏻 😭 😢 I felt sad not being able to help someone who was in need
replyContent: Dear User, we are extremely sorry for the inconvenience. To help you with this, we would like to know your feedback in detail. Kindly write to us at info@bemyeyes.com. We will help you as soon as possible!

content: This is the real experience behind support in the blind community and Making connections I never knew was possible! So far I have had 4 experiences with calls. My latest one was sadly answered quicker by someone else. On my first support call, the person was looking to ensure they looked good for a date. Not only could I say she was stunning but I was also in the meeting with an Ojibwe Alder who is then able to talk about body positivity and loving ourselves in our own skin. 5 stars

Much like what Bart Ouwerkerk said 5 days ago in his Jan.25,'21 review, I absolutely LOVED the idea of this app. My maternal grandmother was at the forefront of Braille translation, doing thousands of papers & books into Braille for many decades until she passed in 1974, & this app/idea felt like a tiny connection to her - a simple, fine way to assist the visually challenged. So I installed the app about 2-1/2 years ago. And then?...Zero. Zippo. Zilch! Not *one single call* in well over a year. Living where I do in N.E. of U.S. - a highly populated area of the world & just 25 miles from Manhattan - you'd think there'd be SOMEONE around (w/in 50 mile radius at least, w/so many cities nearby, much less globally!) that needed help at some point, but nope, not a one! Makes me wonder how that's logistically even possible. So I finally deleted it. Somehow, somewhere, something's not right. A real shame, I would've loved to help. Hopefully some are anyway.
