I want to give it 4 stars just because they are helping others who are blind and are trying to make thier life much more easier. But because of some stangers if he gets in problem then nobody will help him except the blind person. But the app is really good and helpfull!
it's a good initiative and a great app. it's been almost a year since I've downloaded it and i still haven't gotten any calls, should i uninstall it cause its eating space on my phone for no reason
Please look into making it possible to choose multiple language options for 1 volunteer account. Would make it easier to cater to a wider range of people.
Very helpful and cannot be compared with other apps. It bridges all sight loss gaps and makes life meaningful.

It has been 10 months since I installed this app. In that time I have helped 1 person. It took all 10 months before it happened and that is a good thing. With over 4 million volunteers and that means there are plenty of people to help. I'll wait happily wait another 10 months if that's what it takes to be there for a stranger.

To the people giving 1 star for never receiving a call... You realize there are ~140,000 blind people using the app and over 2.3 million volunteers? That means you have a 1 in 16 chance of getting a call every time there's a call. No reason to give low ratings.

Without my glasses, I'm considered blind. I've looked for my glasses when I couldn't find them for up to a week. A volunteer helped me find them one of the times... I had to go somewhere I just hope I never loose my glasses and my phone at the same time
Love the concept, but having had the app for 8 months I've only received one call. Would love to be a bit more helpful!

This is a tremendous service! Wonderfully constructed app. Absolutely easy to use! Wonderful tool that fosters global good will and warmth and generosity! Thank you for the opportunity to provide this service.
Lately I've been receiving a lot of calls more then the usual calls. All of them are just erreurs . I mean they are not real calls. I dont know how this could happen . Hope u fix yhis asap
Very fulfilling knowing that i was able to help someone. Gave me a humbling feeling when I considered all the things that I take for granted as someone who isn't visually impaired.

I'm a sighted user of this app and I believe this could be a fantastic tool for anyone with a sight disability. It gives me a little hope for humanity that there are about 10 sighted users for every 1 blind user and that the sighted users are doing this for free.
what an amazing idea, love being able to help even if it's something simple as choosing an outfit or anything, so thoughtful.

I want to give thanks to the developer of Be My Eyes app. You are not only helping the blind community but you also gave other people all over the world a chance to help them too. This is a friendly-user app. I previously worked as an app reviewer and I must say that this is the best app that I have used so far. Salute to the app developer and the volunteers too!

Brilliant! It's a well thought of app. Thank you to the innovators who came up with this and for giving everyone a platform to freely contribute in making this world brighter. Definitely a great platform to share! ❤️
Amazing app! Only thing missing is the ability for volunteers to change their availability, hopefully this is coming in the future.
absolutely amazing idea and a wonderful application for the differently abled. I came across the app on twitter and was astonished by the generosity of random people.

Dear developers, can the ringtone be managed by the volunteers? 1. I found the volume too low. 2. Can I up/down it, as per my availability? Plus the notification seem to disappear quickly, before I can take any action..

This app and service is the moral hight of why technology exists and what we as human beings can do for eachother. The ability to reach out and help someone in the most simplest of ways by taking 5 minutes of your time is beautiful.
I wish I could change the ringtone so I knew what the heck was going on as soon as someone was trying to reach me. I tried to provide this feedback in the app, but the feedback button doesn't work.

I didnt answer a call yet but the idea behind this app is awesome and really good job and thank you to the creators I loved your ideas and if you could do some other apps for the people with the hearing disability it will be really good

I took my first call today to help a gentleman add credit to his heating at home. Although it's a beautiful sunny day outside, the gentleman did not know this, he only knew that it had been minus seven degrees in parts of the UK and he was glad to get his heating on. This app is a brilliant idea and works very well. I am proud to be part of a community that is working to help those who need somebody to be their eyes. This app can make life so much easier for anybody with a visual impairment.
easy to use - ive had two calls since June when i volunteered. both were under 5 minutes, and it is a great joy to be able to help those that need something simple i can do from anywhere.

I'm giving 5 stars just for the great idea behind the app but I've had the app for nearly 6 months now and haven't received a single call. I'm keeping it for the time when hopefully I can help someone but I may be waiting a while

I've only received one call, but in that call I was able to temporarily give sight for an important matter in the life of someone who is sight impaired. It's a comforting feeling to know I was able to assist.

The idea is great but I had to delete it right after reading the privacy statement. Even for the non-profit organisations, I don't like the idea of having my 'personal information' to share arround with third parties. Nope.

Heartwarming! I received my 1st call the day after I added the app. Nervously, I answered the call and was able to help a kind gentleman set his thermostat. Though it was a simple task, it made me realize how blessed I am and how I can be a blessing to others. Keep the calls coming😊

After a long wait I finally had my first call. I had the pleasure of helping a lovely lady from New York identify Christmas cards. The video was a little pixelated at first which worried me but the quality improved after a brief chat and I was able to give the information they required. :)

It's nice when you get a call, from someone who needs help. there are times that one that will be waiting for a call because of the numbers are different between the volunteers and the vision impaired + the blind
On my first call I helped someone make sure that their oven was preset to the correct temperature. I think this is a very rewarding app to install on your phone.

I installed this to help out but there's way more volunteers than helpers needed so after two months and haven't had one notification. So it's a waste of system resources to keep it installed sadly. I guess it's a good problem to have.

would've loved to help someone, but I never got a request and I need space on my phone. definitely way more volunteers, than people needing help so that was a bummer. chances of getting someone is like 1 in 5 thousand.
Recent update breaks app. I get "field is required" error no matter if I try to sign up for email alerts, or select "not now". I'm on Galaxy S10+ and up to date.

It was amazing untill several updates came and ruined everything. EVERYTIME I receive a call and I answer it, the call ends immediately with this damn error of " An unknown error occurred." Fix it for God's sake! My device is Mi Note 10, android version 11

Best app of the year Like over 3million helpers. This restored my faith in humanity and I will be helping. It's amazing to see strangers help other strangers this is amazing and I wish play store puts this on the home page for it to grow bigger. Thank you

This is such a wonderful app! Seeing that we can support each other as a community is so great. I had my first call today and helped a man set the boiler to his preferred temperature. It feels great knowing that you could be of help to someone :)
Easy to answer calls and give someone a bit of help. Just helped a man sort laundry 2 days ago. It's great that a program like this exists & that so many people are willing to help a stranger.

great application to help others but the 2 times I received calls I got disconnected and have server error , not to mention I can barely log to the application every time Hope to fix it soon to be able

I am new user and installed this app today. I want to cheers the initiative that you guys brought up . It's really amazing guys. Feeling proud that I am a volunteer on such a fantastic app. The concept is really amazing.

Gr8 app!! One Feedback - There are lot of blind people require voluntary writer for their exams. People are taking huge money from them for this social work. Check if you can add this feature in app. It will be a great help.
This is the most wholesome and best app in the world! The volunteers heavily outweigh the people who need help, which is the greatest achievement of an app of this kind, ever.

Perhaps the most satisfying app I have. One way that I could be of help. I cannot tell you how content you feel when you are of some use to someone via this app. Reduced the stars as i see blind folks are not even using it. 3L users only. Can we not undertake initiatives that use volunteers to increase usage of this app?
Definitely a very helpful tool. It took a while to get a call but if finally helped someone and it was very rewarding! 🥰

I REALLY love the idea of helping blind or low sighted people all over the world with just a call. Right now its over 2 million volunteers and about 100 thousand low sighted/blind people that could call you and it only takes about 1-5 minutes helping them out. Mostly you get asked simple questions like what color a shirt has for example. It always makes me feel happier after helping a person and maybe even making their day a little better. (Everyone I met so far was really sweet and polite.)

One of the greatest humanitarian projects I have come across. I recently helped a blind woman in Maryland identify the bills in her wallet and it was a great and rewarding interaction. It's so simple to make someone else's day easier and better.

I'm extremely grateful for this service. As my eyes continue to get worse I continue to get more apprehensive. Thanks to this app some of that has subsided. Knowing help is just a phone call away provides a comfort I needed.

Received a call immediately and a woman wanted me to read off a mastercard number she had. I refused as in your privacy policy it states to not provide or give any type of info regarding credit cards. Uninstaling this app as I can see how someone may abuse this app.

This is the most amazing app I have ever come across. The ability to help another person in need weather near or far, small need or large. Whoever created this is a true hero. My only wish is to help whenever I can. Thank you and God bless.

Its a really good apo and it is helpful for those in need but i have been on this app since december 2019 and ive yet to recive a call and its kinda dissapointing because ive waited for so long and there are so many people on the app and yet so little people that need help i think you guys can do better tbh

I just received my first call minutes ago. I assisted him in turning the knobs of his washing machine. For us, it's that simple. To them, it means a lot. I recommend you download this app, too! #BeMyEyes 5/5 😊👍🏼

I remember being ten and wanting to make an app like this. But I never made it. I'm glad someone else did. I'm so excited to help someone!!! Wonderful idea and thank you for doing this for visually impaired people

I never get calls. I've had this app for months and haven't had a single call. I feel like it's useless for me to have this app if I never get the chance to help. Note: I have limited storage on my phone and I often have to uninstall apps I haven't used if I want to install another app.
Just received my first call after installing the app yesterday!! Such an incredible feeling of being able to help someone at random. This world needs more of these amazing apps!
Have had the app since Dec 4th 2019 with 0 calls. I loovvveeee the idea, but haven't been able to help anyone. Gonna keep the app in the off chance but for sure not keeping my hopes up.

Phenomenal concept. It's great to assist and be assisted without the burden of a long process or formality. Hoping many more visually impaired can be financially stable enough to be able to connect with the service in future or that it can become something offered for free by communications companies similar to how they offer social media only plans. 🍻 to the future
A great app and experience. I wish I received more calls because it feels great everytime I'm able to help someone. 🙂
This is an amazing app for the visually disabled. Hatsoff to the people who ideated it and created it. I have been on this just 14 days and already had the chance to help 2 wonderful ladies.
i have gotten to help many people with this app! never a bad experience, all are so sweet and kind. i cannot stop smiling over one of my experiences. she was so nice and understanding.
Outstanding app, but currently has 17 volunteers for each visually impaired user, so you don't get many calls at all.
Have only been lucky enough to receive one call so far, but wow, talk about humbling! I helped a sweet woman match an outfit. I realized real quick how much I take for granted. Beautiful app!
Awesome app. Awards should be given to the creator. I 100% recommend it and wish that more visually disabled people were aware that it was available as a resource to them. ⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐
Loved the concept and Idea. Downloaded the app, but can't get past creating an account, i keep gettin "an unknown error has ocurred"........
replyContent: Hello Paulo, we apologise for the issue you are having. You are welcome to reach our tech support from info@bemyeyes.com. Hope to see you soon!

content: I just saw the ad on YouTube. I haven't downloaded/used the app yet. I'm only rating it 5-stars because of the concept and it's brilliant. Cheers to the developers. Great work.
I received my first call today. It was smooth, quick and about as simple as it can be. Thank you to the developers for a great and intuitive app.
Haven't had my first call yet, so I cannot give feedback regarding the matching process. I wish there was a function to set times for when we are available and not.
Had my first opportunity to help someone see some numbers they needed. The call was quick and easy and the feeling of being there to help someone in need was priceless!
Using this app for almost six months now and I do get calls frequently nowadays. It feels so good and satisfying to help nameless strangers just because I can.

I'm a native French Canadian so I can speak both english and french and they give me an option to do so witch is great, also I feel great to help, If I can't answer I just don't, for now I got one call every week or so.

Got my first call today I answered but was black screen and no audio coming through either. I had a good connection too. I don't know what the problem was but I'm gutted I hope they got the help :( xx
Fantastic app. I am a sighted person and have had numerous interactions with sight impared people around the world.
I'm bilingual and I could help more people than only the ones that speak the language I selected. It would be better to be able to select more languages than just one.
This is great ! Awsome !! For people who want to help people wanting assistance, as we all do at one point in time in our lives !!! GREAT WORK ....ACTUAL USING TECHNOLOGY IN A AMAZING WAY !!
I think the idea of the program is amazing. I think the only thing is left to do is to find a way to increase a number of users who have problems with vision. And we volunteers can help with this.
Smart move guys, this is one way to help a lot of people, without being an inconvenience to anyone, it's quick, simple, and brings a ton of smiles!

Beautiful App. Probably the best idea ever since the invention of internet. So far I only got to answer one call and it made my day. Something so simple and so extremely useful. Thank you for making that happen. ❤

I made my first call today to receive help. The volunteer was so kind and patient with me. My call was to test the capability of this app and how it can help me with my very first trip alone out of state as someone that is blind. Thank you Be My Eyes. I would not be able to do this without you.
terms of service & privacy policy could not be accessed. they are just words on the screen. there isn't a link connected
Just had my first call to help a gentleman. He needed help picking out the colors for his clothes. Awesom app. Clear video and audio. Great experience. Thank you for putting this app together.
Nit onky does this help visually impared people but it's nice to feel helpful. It's a super quick and easy way to help someone out

You will never regret using this app to help someone! It is the most amazing feeling to be able to see for someone who has impaired vision. Volunteer to help someone else today - it will help you, too!
I have helped some people and can't answer some phone calls. It is frustrating as I try to swipe with no answer as my app will not respond. Frustrating!!!
Thank you for priceless opportunity to be someone's eyes. The video call went well. I will learn more languages in order to be able to help more people. Best regards, Jum.
Awesome app. If you have vision problems, you can have a random person somewhere in the world help you at the touch of a button. If you don't have vision problems, you can help people who do.
The last few times I've gotten a call, I answer and then the call ends. Idk if this is normal or there's something wrong on my app or phone? I haven't connected with anyone yet, I'd like to though.
I've only had one call but it absolutely made my day to speak to Ashley and assist her... This app is above and beyond amazing and I can't wait for my next call! 😁

Just signed up as a volunteer. This is such a fantastic initiatve for both those with needs and those who are happy to help those in need. I have encouraged my family and friends to sign up to volunteer and my visually impaired sister as someone in need.
I got one of my first calls today but it didn't show that it came from this app... I searched through almost all of my apps before I could close the call as it woke me up early.

I haven't gotten a call yet. Admin says may take a week or two before I get a call, due to the fact that there are only oh-so-many people that need help, vs the 2 MILLION volunteers (a testament to humanity). Some apps make you wait hours, days, weeks before you can progress to "the next level". This is one app that... Well, I just don't mind waiting for. When my call comes, I'll be honored to help!
Just got my first call and I answered but there was just a message for a few minutes saying trying to connect. I couldn't hear anyone. I hope the person was able to find help anyway.

Should a stop and start time option. And a flagging option as well, like every other service you will spammer, scammers and just bad people. Upon fixing that you will get 5stars.. great idea! Congrats!
Just took my first call for help and only had the app installed a couple of days. Wow, really useful app and the caller just needed 30 seconds of my time and I'm so pleased I could help
Good idea but I answered my first call today and the app wouldn't show me the video just the loading symbol and "trying to connect call". Why is it doing that and how do I fix it?
Great idea. But I kept it on my phone for over a year and besides a few "marketing" or awareness notifications, never got a request.

So i got this app a few days ago and i got my First Call but once i answered it logged me off and said there was an error. :( theres nothing to do with my connection. I love the app but i hope this wont happen again.
I think this is s brilliant idea, but I've received two calls in (what feels like) a year and both times I couldn't answer. It just says "trying to answer" but never does.
I have recieved 2 calls and it went perfectly both times. Its really nice to be able to help with things seeing people take for granted every single day.

im beyond amazed! got my 1st call in 24hrs of downloading. helped a woman pick eye shadow. its easy and very helpful to peoplr who are blind or close to. youll feel so happy n proud. just do it and help!
I've had a couple of calls and I love being able to help! I did have to click the small screen at the bottom after I answered a call in order to see the video.
Great idea but I had it installed for over 8 months and I only got one call at the beginning and the app crashed when I tapped to answer.
This app is awesome! I can honestly say this app is extremely helpful and the live assistants are quick, friendly and knowledgeable. This app has helped my daily life struggles!
(I'm a sighted person) I've only gotten a few calls so far and each time I've tried to answer them, I've gotten an error message and the call drops. Anyone else had this issue?
Wonderful idea! But please improve the video call quality. Sometimes its hard to see due to bad pixels.

I waited and waited to be asked for help by anyone in need through this app and was never required even once and so after having given it more than enough time, I ended up deleting it thinking it might possibly have been some kinda 'con' in some way. Disappointed.
replyContent: Hello Holly, thank you for the support! Since we have 3+ million volunteers, it might take time to get a call. All we can ask for is your patience, we hope you will catch a call quite soon. In the meantime you can help spread the word about Be My Eyes in your local community, so we can welcome more blind and low-vision users!

content: So, I downloaded it yesterday and didn't knew when a call would come, it just did and I got to help someone and I have the best feeling ever rn! Please please please download it and be someon's sight. This is one of the best app to ever exist...
This is a really good app. It is straightforward to use and visually appealing. I enjoy volunteering and helping how I can. Great idea.
Whenever i get a call from someone the screen stays black and i can't see what is the person want to show me, and it feels bad not to be able to help after i get the call

I like this app very much. A good way to help people. If you are alone at your home or any other place and feeling bour then you should use this app to help blind people to get pleasure. I really get pleasure by helping people. In this app we can let our eyes to blind ones because eyes are a huge gift from Allah Almighty to us. We should help people to get pleasure. This is a good app. ⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐
Everytime I try to answer a call there's an unexpected error or it just doesn't answer. I'd much rather be helping people, the app needs work.

There needs to be more guidance apps like this to help disabled people. If you're visually impaired, there are people ready to help. In my opinion people should be vetted before volunteering just to prevent abuse. But that's my only concern. For those not getting any calls, it took me 3 months, its normal as theres millions of helpers and only hundreds of thousands impaired people

Love this app. Although i did delete it because there are soooo many volunteers in comparison to folks who needs help so after a month of having the app and not getting anyone i deleted it for the space.

Hi I am a volunteer i just want to suggest that there are some of us that are bilingual that are capable to cater two or more languages so if it's possible can you let us use 2 language insted of just choosing one thanks.
Be my eyes is amazing app. I really liked and appreciated that how much technology can make one's lives so easy and independent..
I got a call but could only hear the person. Couldn't see them on the screen as it was black displaying "trying to answer call" So frustrating 😑
The only reason I won't give this app 5 stars is because when I try to give feedback on my call, the Problem button doesn't work but the Good button does, which is disingenuous.
AN ABSOLUTELY AMAZING APP! I am so happy to be able to help someone. I am grateful to of stumbled onto this app and will share it any and every chance i get. it humbles me greatly to be needed!!!
The app won't allow me to sign in but I like what the creators of the app tried to do. Hopefully this error can be fixed because I really want to help.

I'm so happy that this kind of thing exists. My Dad was completely blind, and as he passed away in '95 there wasn't anything like this, but I know it would have been a massive help to him. The fact that random strangers are willing and able to give their time to help others in need is just fantastic, and it gives me hope for humanity.

The concept is great, however I started in JULY of 2019 and havent received one call. So its basically been sitting there useless. It's always open on my phone just in case. Props to the idea, poor execution.
I haven't gotten a call yet, but my rating is purely based on the app idea alone! I love this and I'm so blessed to be a part of something so amazing!!! I can't wait for my first call!!!!!!
i love this app it actually one of the greatest apps ever. when you can help someone it gives you a great feeling, some feeling that i can't even describe.
I feel so helpful, can't believe I received the second phone call and was able to help, .its a great app. Hope to see more apps like this one, thanks to the founder of it
Please make a time frame that people are able to help. I can't answer while I'm at work or sleeping! Also, this app needs a better notification system

It was on my old phone and today I realised that it was not on my new one. So, I have installed it this morning and got a call. It was such a good feeling to help someone who is in need. God has given us so many things that we have to be thankful about and thanks for all who helped to realise this app.

we need to make sure this app is spread far and wide. The number of blind compared to the volunteers is low so you aren't harassed but when you do get that call and manage to help it gives you a huge smile for the rest of the day knowing you have done good.
I waited 1 year and 4 months to finally get my first call and I was so elated to be able to help someone out! What a great experience it was. He was grateful, and so was I! Such an awesome app!

I've only ever gotten one ring that someone else beat me to answering, but I have a friend with a brain tumor who is using the app to live as normally as possible without feeling like he's taking advantage of family and friends. It's a big relief to him.
An excellent concept! But I fully agree not to be monitored by any public members there are very evil people out there and can easily give you just the opposite info that you realy need.
Such an awesome way to give back! It takes such little effort to help somebody and makes so much difference. EVERYONE should be able to take 5 minutes out of their time to answer a call. 💜

Thanks to the creators will always be here if anyone needs my help. maybe i'm not updated but how do blind people navigate their phone? i used Android talkback. wasn't easy. still nice to create value for impaired people. 👍🏼
The idea seems very promising, but there's not much to the app. I think there should at least be more options so that you can set a certain time of day or something that you're available.

My first call went very well. It was such a wonderful opportunity to be able to help someone. There are way more volunteers than those that need help so don't expect a call right away or a lot of calls.
I'd like to to use this app, but the terms of service aren't viewable in the app before clicking "I agree". Failed before it even started.

I love helping others! I was so excited when I received my first call! Unfortunately, I missed the one that came in today 😔 I really look forward to those calls. Great opportunity for individuals who may need assistance.

Hello. Just called a voluteer because I needed help to reset my hands on my watch. She said she can't see nothing so I told her to turn on the torch because all volunteers can do that. Well she said she couldn't turn on a torch which is full of rubbish. I guess I'm now uninstalling this app, blind people, don't get it!
replyContent: Hello, we are sorry for the experience you had. Be My Eyes has a feature that allows volunteers to turn on the torch during a call. Please consider making another call when such a thing happens.

content: Seems to be very helpful for the visually impaired. The app itself is extremely easy to use to help.
I had this app for a year and never recieved any call. I genuinely think that its good intention tho. I have to uninstall to give additional space to my phone.

You rarely get called, but that's a good thing. I've had the app for almost 4 years and I've only gotten a chance to help 2 people. This app is a great way to do something small to help someone in need.
This is such an amazing app. I feel a sense of importance, even if, just for one person, every once and a while. Please volunteer ❤️
Fantastic app! My only issue is that I've had it on my phone for years but only ever received one call to help someone out.
I downloaded the app 5 months ago, I got one call a month ago, an it was one of the best experiences of my life. The joy of helping another human being is incredibly exciting.
After a year I finally got my first call today and the app wouldn't let me hit the answer button Super frustrating. Love the concept but needs work

This apps is very good,,you can ask whatever question you want and they will answers,,you also can ask them to read and they'll read perfectly and nicely,,oh btw the replier is not a robot,it's human,when we want to ask something,,it almost like we're in video call but they'll not show our face,,i really² love this apps💗😍 i wanna say a lot of thanks for those who created this apps😆
What an amazing app! After over a year of having the app, i finally got a call. It was such an amazing experience and great conversation.
Such a brilliant app to assist the blind or partially blind. I would like more calls assigned to me. These acts of kindness warm my heart.

I received my first call today. I was so excited, I was at work and stepped away just to have the experience. The gentleman I worked with was very nice and I feel completely fulfilled helping him. It has taken me 6-7 months to have that first experience, but it has been well worth the wait! I'm looking forward to the next one.
So far I have only received 1 call but it made my day to be able to help someone! And answering the call was super easy! Great app and idea!
such an amazing idea, and wonderful execution by the dev team! simple, but powerful. haven't had a crash or bug to report thus far!
Fantastic app for helping others. The fact that there are so many more volunteers opposed to those who need assistance gives me hope for humanity...
Amazing app! I was so excited when I got my first call, and I felt absolutely elated after helping my caller. The creator of this app is a genius!
I love this app. Although I've only ever received one phone call. Wish I could be of more help but good to know there is more than enough help out there for the visually impaired who use this app.

Great idea, but I told my blind friends about it and it turns out they would have to pay to access the app. I have an Android and I'm guessing they are using iPhones. The blind should be exempt from the fee. I don't want to use it if they are not.
replyContent: Hi Kai, our app is completely free both on Android and iOS, for both volunteers and blind/low vision users no matter how much they use it.

content: It may take a while to get a call, but be patient. There are a lot of volunteers, 4M. I so far have helped one individual. It was a great experience and worth the wait. Took almost a month to get my first call.
I think this is a helpful app for the blind. It can help blind people a lot and can make a great change in thier lives. With the help of this app they can be helped with many things.
Couldn't help caller due to app issue... Video wouldn't load, so couldn't help caller with what they couldn't see. It's a shame... I hope it will get fixed!
I absolutely LOVE helping people see their world. If you have difficulty seeing or cannot see at all, please give this app a try--I'd love to be your eyes! 💟
Just signed up as a volunteer. It's so easy and fast to get started, only took about two minutes once the app downloaded!
Been a volunteer for a few months and got some calls. Feels good to be of help to those in need. Great initiative, and a great app. 10/10
Update broke this app for me. It wants me to subscribe and when I press sign up it says "This field is required" when there's no field for me to fill anything in.
The visuals never came through on my first call and on my second it was stuck on "trying to answer call" and never successfully connected.
I helped a man today pick out a jumper for his wife in hospital. Only a small act that took less than a couple of minutes but hopefully put a smile on both of their faces. Great idea this app is
I helped my first person it was great! I wish, there was a way to set the app to only vibrate when I get a call though because I woke up from sleeping to answer it.
